title: Otuk Creek Stream Discharge Data (Excel) [Hinzman, L.]

The stream discharge was monitored several times a day during snowmelt and periodically after snowmelt until late summer by taking individual measurements using a Flowmate current meter and a wading rod. Data is provided as an Excel spreadsheet and separated by year.

title: HLY-08-03 DMSP Satellite Images [Sambrotto/LDEO]
summary: This dataset includes images from the Defense Meteorological Satellites Program (DMSP) satellites. The images are from the satellite passes that occurred over the Bering Sea during the US Coast Guard Cutter Healy Bering Sea Ecosystem Study-Bering Sea Integrated Ecosystem Research Program (BEST-BSIERP) 2008 0803 (summer) cruise. BEST-BSIERP together are the Bering Sea project. The images are from the F12, F13, F14, F15 and F16 satellites and include 1 km visible, 4 km visible and infrared (IR), and total ice products and are in jpeg format.

title: Council Climate Data - Shrub Site (Excel) [Beringer, J.]
summary: This dataset includes climate data from the shrub site area in the Council region gathered during the 2000 summer field season in Excel format.

title: COMET CASE 037 Surface Airways Observations

title: COMET CASE 010 WSR-88D Radial Velocity (lowest tilt angle) from Wichita, KS (ICT)
summary: This dataset contains the velocity relative to radar (lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the Wichita, KS (ICT) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: Oil Industry Zooplankton Ecology Data [Hopcroft]
summary:
The primary objective of the planktonic communities program is to describe spatial, seasonal and interannual characteristics of the plankton (phytoplankton and zooplankton) communities within the study areas.

Phytoplankton, along with algae that grow attached to sea ice, are the conduit of the sun's energy into organic "food" at the base of the food chain in the Chukchi Sea. Phytoplankton are assessed as chlorophyll-a concentration from water samples collected with a Conductivity, Temperature, Depth (CTD) rosette. We also measure the concentration of the major nutrients required for their growth in these samples. Zooplankton are the major consumers of phytoplankton, and hence the key pathway to vertebrates such as pelagic fish, seabirds, and even bowhead whales. Zooplankton are collected using two different methods: paired ring nets of medium-size mesh hauled vertically at slow speed for smaller species, and Bongo nets towed off the side of a ship moving at 2 knots for larger, faster species. This dataset is part of the Pacific Marine Arctic Regional Synthesis (PacMARS) Project.

This dataset contains the original CSV files, metadata files, shapefiles, and geodatabase files in ZIP files.

summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Radial Velocity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  CENTRAL PENNSYLVANIA (CCX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

summary: This dataset contains data from  NCEP's Medium Range Forecast (MRF) Model. The model runs are for 00Z with forecasts given every 12 hours and going out 10 days.  The data are archived in GRIB gridded files.

title: Mobile Integrated Profiling System (MIPS) SODAR Imagery [U Alabama]
summary: This dataset contains Profiler/Sodar Mobile Integrated Profiling System (MIPS) SODAR Image Data from the University of Alabama in Huntsville.

title: Diode Laser Hygrometer (DLH) Measurements
summary: This dataset contains Diode Laser Hygrometer (DLH) measurements of water vapor (H2O(v)) collected on the NASA DC-8 aircraft from the High Ice Water Content (HIWC) Radar Study project that took place in Fort Lauderdale, Florida; Palmdale, California; and Kona, Hawaii. The data files are in ICARTT format.

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Land Characterization: EDC NASA Landsat Pathfinder
summary: The North American Landscape Characterization (NALC) project is a collaborative effort between the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) and the U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) to provide complete coverage of the conterminous U.S. and Mexico for the purposes of mapping land cover and land cover change.

title: R/V Seward Johnson Rawinsonde Data [UNOLS]
summary: This is one of the upper air data sets developed for the Rain in Cumulus Over the Ocean (RICO) project. This data set includes the high vertical resolution (2 second) rawinsonde data from the Research Vessel (R/V) Seward Johnson. A total of 88 soundings were released from 31 December 2004 to 24 January 2005. Soundings were typically released four to six times per day.

title: GTS Mandatory/Significant Level Sounding Data (ESC Format)
summary: This data set includes the quality controlled GTS soundings for two High Ice Water Content (HIWC) Radar 2018 observational periods and regions. The first was around Florida for the period of 30 July to 12 August 2018 and the second was across southern California, Baja, and Hawaii for the period 11-30 August 2018. This data set includes only those stations in the regions for which high vertical resolution data were not available. Those stations with high resolution data are available in a separate data set. A total of 281 quality-controlled, mandatory and significant level resolution soundings are contained in the final data set.

title: GCIP/ESOP-98 Surface: Cook County/Imperial Valley Precipitation
summary: The Cook County and Imperial Valley Precipitation are available off-line via a remote link to the Illinois State Water Survey (ISWS). The researcher should contact Bob Scott of the ISWS to obtain these data. Please see this dataset's contact information.

title: Stomach contents of birds collected at sea (B77)
summary: This dataset contains data on the dissected stomach contents of birds collected in waters within 200 kilometers of the Pribilof Islands, St. George and St. Paul and extending southeastward to Bogoslof Island in 2008 and 2009. Birds were collected by shotgun and tissue samples of cheek feather, muscle, and liver were removed for stable isotope analyses. Whole stomachs were sent frozen to University of Alaska Fairbanks for identification. The carcasses were re-frozen immediately after organ and feather tissue removal, and stored at Moss Landing Marine Laboratories for further studies.

title: TSI 3025 and Scanning Mobility Particle Sizer (SMPS) Data
summary: This dataset contains total particle counts from the TSI 3025 and particle size distributions (dN/dlogDp vs. Dp) from the SMPS data for the 6 research flights of Airborne Research Instrumentation Testing Opportunity (ARISTO- 2016). Both are in ICARTT file format. Additional information about detection limits, flags, diameter bins, etc. are in the headers of the files. The 3025 did not operate during RF01, so the data is all filled in by -9999. Please see the included readme file for more information.

title: COMET CASE 039 WSR-88D Storm Total Precipitation Estimate from DES MOINES, IA
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Storm Total Precipitation Estimate data product archived from the  DES MOINES, IA (DMX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: Mexico Navy SEMAR Automated Weather Station Data
summary:
This dataset contains automated weather station data from the Mexican Navy SEMAR stations that are located along the coast of Mexico and its islands.

More information on the network can be found at http://meteorologia.semar.gob.mx/. This web site is in Spanish.

title: Forward-Looking Digital Camera Imagery
summary: During HIPPO-3, the GV_N677F flew a forward looking digital camera for in-flight video capture. Individual photo jpeg images were captured once per second during flights. Images taken after dark have been stripped from this archive. The remaining images have been combined into hour long tarfiles running from zero minutes zero seconds (or the start time of the first file) to 23 minutes 59 seconds (or the end time of the last file) after each hour. Note that the first and last tarfile for each flight will contain less than a full hour of imagery. Directory files returned with each order give the contents of each corresponding tar file.

summary: This dataset contains the velocity relative to radar (third-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the Los Angeles, CA (VTX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

summary: This dataset contains the Coordinated Energy and Water Cycle Observation Project (CEOP) CATCH streamgauge data.  The data set contains hourly data for the CEOP time period.

title: Left-Looking Digital Camera Imagery
summary: During SOCRATES-TEST, the NSF/NCAR HIAPER GV (Tail Number N677F) flew a left looking digital camera for in-flight video capture. Individual photo jpeg images were captured once per second during flights. Images taken after dark have been stripped from this archive. The remaining images have been combined into hour long tarfiles running from zero minutes zero seconds (or the start time of the first file) to 23 minutes 59 seconds (or the end time of the last file) after each hour. Note that the first and last tarfile for each flight will contain less than a full hour of imagery. Directory files returned with each order give the contents of each corresponding tar file.

title: Surface Meteorological (5-minute) Multi-Network Composite [NCAR/EOL]
summary: This data set contains five-minute resolution surface meteorological data in National Center for Atmospheric Research/Earth Observing Laboratory (NCAR/EOL) Quality Control (QC) format from stations within the following networks: Oklahoma Mesonet, National Center for Atmospheric Research (NCAR) Atmospheric Technology Division (ATD) Integrated Surface Flux Facility (ISFF), Texas Tech Wext Texas Mesonet (WTXMESO), United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) Agricultural Research Service (ARS) Micronet, and the 5 minute surface data extracted from the IHOP_2002 Mesonet 1-Minute Surface Meteorological Composite. Data for the International H2O Project 2002 (IHOP 2002) domain (32N to 42N latitude and 90W to 105W longitude) and time period (13 May 2002 through 25 June 2002) are contained within this dataset. This dataset contains data from 261 stations. In July 2005 the Oklahoma Climatological Survey reprocessed and updated the Oklahoma Mesonet surface meteorological data. EOL has not updated the composite files, however the newer OKMESO data is available.

title: UAF Moored Acoustic Doppler Current Profiler (ADCP) Data
summary:
As part of the Bering Sea Ecosystem Study-Bering Sea Integrated Ecosystem Research Program (BEST-BSIERP), a family of oceanographic moorings were anchored to the bottom on the eastern Bering Sea in the summer 2008. They were recovered and redeployed in 2009, and the final recovery occurred in the summer of 2010.

This data set contains the data for 2008-2010 from the Acoustic Doppler Current Profiler (ADCP) in zip archives by mooring: C25, C40, N25, N40, N55, S25, and S40.

In reports and publications that use these data, please acknowledge their source: T. Weingartner, University of Alaska Fairbanks, NSF Grant ARC-0732771.

BEST-BSIERP together are the Bering Sea project.

title: Citation Aircraft Flight Parameters
summary: This dataset contains the Citation aircraft flight parameter data collected for the INDOEX 1999 project area and time of interest. Please see the data files and the readme documentation for a complete list of the parameters included in this dataset.

title: NRL P-3 ELDORA Radar [NCAR/EOL]
summary: The Electra Doppler Radar (ELDORA) is an airborne, dual beam, meteorological research radar developed jointly by NCAR and France's Centre de Recherches en Physique de L'Environnement Terrestre et Planetaire (CRPE). The ELDORA radar operated during T-PARC/TCS08 on the NRL-P3 aircraft for 23 research flights from 12 August to 4 October 2008. The data are in DORADE (Doppler Radar Exchange) sweep files tarred into 10 minute chunks.

title: Polar Bears: Adipose analyses
summary: From a subset of captured bears a sample of adipose tissue was collected via tissue biopsy. These tissues were analyzed for lipid content, percent of saturated fatty-acids, fatty-acid profiles, as well as stable carbon isotope values. Information on bear IDs and dates of capture is not available because of the threatened species status of the subjects.

title: Low Rate (LRT - 1 sps) Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics Flight-Level Data
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the NSF/NCAR QueenAir, B-80 aircraft (Tail Number N306D) during the NEWS-82 project. This dataset contains low rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in netCDF format.

title: ACE-1: Satellite GMS-5 IR A/C TRACK Images (GIF)
summary: GMS-5 Infrared (IR) imagery (with aircraft track overlaid on plot) collected during the ACE-1 intensive operations in Hobart, Tasmania, from the Australian Bureau of Meteorology. These images consist of the Southern Ocean (image center 30 deg S, 140 deg E), 8 km resolution, collected every hour. Digital McIDAS area format data files were collected hourly by OFPS from which these GIF images were created.

title: DOTSTAR ASTRA NCAR/EOL Dropsonde Constant Level Winds KML Data
summary: This data set contains Google Earth KML files that contain constant level wind observations derived from the dropsondes released from the DOTSTAR Astra jet. These files were produced by NCAR/EOL from the real time GTS TEMPDROP messages and have not been quality controlled.

title: COMET CASE 041 MOS Data
summary: This dataset contains model data from aviation, mrf, and ngm model runs. Data is archived in GEMPAK formatted files. Data  is available at 12Z and 00Z.

title: Kuparuk Basin Watershed Studies [Kane, D., L. Hinzman]
summary: This is an external link to a University of Alaska Fairbanks (UAF) Water and Environmental Research Center (WERC) website where Kuparuk Basin watershed studies data and documentation can be found. This page provides access to hydrology and environmental climate data from research sites spanning from the Northern foothills of the Brooks Range to the Coastal Plain of Alaska, near Prudhoe Bay. Most sites are within the Kuparuk River watershed. This material is based upon work supported by the National Science Foundation under Grants No. OPP-9318535, OPP-9214927 and OPP-9814984.

title: Wyoming Cloud Lidar Data
summary: This dataset provides a link to the University of Wyoming King Air Data Archive location for the Wyoming Cloud Lidar data and quick look plots for the PECAN deployment.

title: NWS Storm Prediction Center Watch Boxes, Warning, and Storm Report Imagery [NCAR/EOL]
summary: This dataset contains NWS Storm Prediction Center Watch Boxes, Warnings, and Storm Report Imagery from the VORTEX2 2009 and 2010 Field Catalogs. Imagery files are only available for the VORTEX2 field phases for approximately May-June 2009 and April-June 2010. The files are gif images. See the catalog links below to access the field catalogs.

title: COMET CASE 019 WSR-88D Base Reflectivity (lowest tilt angle) from OKLAHOMA CITY, OK/Altus AFB
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Base Reflectivity (lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  OKLAHOMA CITY, OK/Altus AFB (FDR) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: NCAR HSRL lidar data (CfRadial)
summary:
This dataset contains High Spectral Resolution Lidar (HSRL) data collected aboard the NSF/NCAR GV HIAPER (Gulfstream-V High-performance Instrumented Airborne Platform for Environmental Research) (N677F) during the SOCRATES (Southern Ocean Clouds, Radiation, Aerosol Transport Experimental Study) project from 15 January 2018 to 24 February 2018.  The data are in CfRadial format and are available as tar archives. This data set contains all HSRL variables and is geared towards a more advanced lidar data user. A data set which contains only the primary HSRL variables at a 2Hz resolution (and also data from the HIAPER Cloud Radar (HCR)) which is geared towards the general user is available at the link in the Related links" section below.

"

title: WRF 4KM Radar Reflectivity Forecast Imagery (Jackson to Douglas) [Dudhia (NCAR-MMM)]
summary: This dataset contains Weather Research and Forecasting Model (WRF) 4 kilometer vertical cross-sections of radar reflectivity from Jackson, WY to Douglas, WY. The imagery was generated during the ICE-L project and is in PNG format. It covers the time span from 2007-11-19 00:00:00 to 2007-12-21 23:59:59.

title: GCIP/ESOP-96 Surface: Daily Precipitation Composite
summary: The Daily Precipitation Composite was formed from several data sources (i.e., Arkansas-Red Basin River Forecast Center, National Weather Service Cooperative Observers Precipitation data, and the precipitation data extracted from the ESOP-96 Hourly Precipitation Composite). Data from these sources were quality controlled and merged to form this precipitation composite.

title: COMET CASE 018 WSR-88D Radial Velocity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) from SIOUX FALLS, SD
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Radial Velocity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  SIOUX FALLS, SD/Sioux Falls (FSD) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: RELAMPAGO Mobile Ground Asset KML Data
summary: This data set contains the real time geolocation information for the mobile ground assets that provided their location information via Delorme GPS devices for the RELAMPAGO Field Catalog. The frequency of the location data varied depending on the settings used by each vehicle. The assets include the CSWR DOW/COW/probes and the mobile radiosonde units from CSU and UIUC. These data have not been quality checked.

title: USAF C-130 HDOB GTS Messages [NCAR/EOL]
summary: This data set includes 1450 HDOB messages from the two USAF C-130 aircraft that flew during the ITOP field program. The C-130 aircraft were based out of Guam and flew around tropical systems in the western Pacific Ocean during August-October 2010. The data are in the GTS HDOB format. NCAR/EOL have conducted no quality control on these data files.

title: COMET CASE 013 NCEP Medium Range Forecast Model
summary: This dataset contains data from NCEP's Medium Range Forecast (MRF) model run on 23  Feb. 1998. The model runs are for 00Z with forecasts given every 12 hours and going out ten days.

summary: NULL

title: STORM-FEST L2D2 5-Millibar Dropsondes
summary: About 96 NCAR L2D2 dropwindsondes were deployed during STORM-FEST. Data consists of interpolated 5 mb interval pressure, temperature, relative humidity and wind speed/ direction.

title: ASC Mini-SoDAR Ten Minute Average Data at North West Granite Site (SOD-NWG)
summary: This dataset contains ASC Mini-SoDAR Ten Minute Average data collected at the North West Granite Site (SOD-NWG) during the Mountain Terrain Atmospheric Modeling and Observations (MATERHORN-X) program.

title: FAAM BAe-146 Meteorology and Navigation Data
summary: A link is provided to the CEDA Archive of FAAM BAe-146 archive of core and non-core instrumentation from the aircraft for the VOCALS campaign.

title: HLY-09-01 POSMV and Navigation Data [Cooper, L./LDEO]
summary:
This dataset includes files that the POSMV Navigation computer logged onboard the U.S. Coast Guard Cutter Healy during the Bering Sea Ecosystem Study-Bering Sea Integrated Ecosystem Research Program (BEST-BSIERP) 2009 0901 (early spring) cruise. BEST-BSIERP together are the Bering Sea project. The data are from various navigation devices and from devices related to the Seabeam system. There are also event files in this dataset that are from various systems. The event files show the start and stop times and various events in the recording and setup history of the device. The individual data files are collected into tar files by day. The following is a list of the devices:

adu5 - Ashtech GPS data;
aggps - Trimble AGGPS data;
ais - Automatic Identification System messages;
bgm221 - BGM221 Gravimeter;
bgm222 - BGM222 Gravimeter;
ibs_waypoints - Bridge IBS Navigation System Way Points data;
mk27 - MK27 Sperry Gyroscope data;
mk39 - MK39 Sperry Gyroscope data;
posatt - POSMV Attitude data;
posnav - POSMV GPS data;
posreform2sb - Reformatted POSMV data for Seabeam;
sbctr - Seabeam center beam data;
sbsv - Seabeam surface sound velocity data;
tsg_met - SIO TSG and Met sensor data;
winch_aft - Aft A Frame winch data;
winch_stbd - Starboard A Frame winch data

title: BALTEX: Lindenberg Soil Heat Flux Raw Data (10 min)
summary: This is the 10 minute soil heat flux data for the Baltex Lindenberg Site.

title: FP3 Millersville University Surface Meteorology and Radiation Data
summary: This data set contains one minute observations of several surface meteorological and radiation parameters obtained by the Millersville University WeatherPak 2000 tower located at the PECAN Fixed PISA 3 site in Ellis, Kansas. The data are in excel files that contain daily plots as well.

title: COMET CASE 018 WSR-88D Base Reflectivity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) from GREEN BAY, WI
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Base Reflectivity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  GREEN BAY, WI/Ashwaubenon (GRB) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: GCIP/LSA-NW 00 Surface: Montana's RWIS Miscellaneous Precipitation
summary: The Montana's Remote Weather Informational System (RWIS) Miscellaneous Precipitation dataset is one of several datasets provided in the GEWEX Continental-Scale International Project (GCIP) Large Scale Area-North West (LSA-NW) Enhanced Annual Observing Period (EAOP) 2000. Data from this source are provided as is in their original format and were not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS. This dataset contains the available data for the GCIP LSA-NW EAOP-00 domain and time period (01 April 2000 through 31 March 2001). The GCIP LSA-NW EAOP-00 domain is approximately 90W to 115W longitude and 36N to 51N latitude.

title: MP1 OU/NSSL CLAMPS MWR and Surface Meteorology Data
summary: This data set contains brightness temperature, precipitable water vapor, and liquid water path measurements from the Microwave Radiometer (MWR) that was aboard the PECAN Mobile PISA 1 OU/NSSL CLAMPS vehicle. This data set also includes surface meteorology observations from the met station that was about 1 m above the CLAMPS trailer. Measurements were made at locations around the central US for most PECAN IOPs and UFOs.

title: ASOS 1-minute Data
summary: This data set contains the 1-minute resolution observations from the Automated Surface Observing System (ASOS) network of ~860 stations in the contiguous United States. These data were collected and archived by the National Centers for Environmental Information (NCEI; formerly the National Climatic Data Center). These data are provided as is, NCAR/EOL has conducted no processing or quality control on these data.

title: ORCAS Field Catalog Models/Analyses Products
summary: This dataset provides a link to the ORCAS Field Catalog Models Products section which includes imagery from several models during the campaign.

title: NEXRAD MAF (Midland/Odessa, TX) Reflectivity and Velocity Imagery
summary: This dataset includes NEXRAD Reflectivity and Velocity Imagery from the VORTEX2 field catalogs for 2009 and 2010. These imagery products are taken from the NEXRAD station located in Midland/Odessa, TX. The files are in .gif format.  Imagery files are only available for the VORTEX2 field phases for approximately May-June 2009 and April-June 2010. See the related links below to access the field catalogs for the exact time periods covered by this data set.

title: Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics HRT Data in GENPROI format
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the QueenAir, A-80 aircraft (Tail Number N304D) during the NBL project. This dataset contains high rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in GENPRO-I format.

title: COMET CASE 006 WSI NIDS Composite Reflectivity from Green Bay, WI
summary: This dataset contains the composite reflectivity data product archived from the WSI NIDS datastream for  the Green Bay, WI radar. Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format.

title: HIAPER Cloud Radar (HCR) Field Moments data in cfRadial format
summary: This dataset contains HIAPER Cloud Radar (HCR) Field Moments data collected during the SAANGRIA Test project from 14 February 2013 to 3 March 2013. The data are in cfRadial format and are available as large tar files (one per flight).

title: COMET CASE 024 ACARS data
summary: This dataset contains ACARS data. Data is archived as netCDF files.

title: TOGA COARE soundings from Singapore
summary: This dataset consists of sounding data from Singapore (WMO 48698) which was operated by the Singapore Meteorology Office. Soundings were taken four times per day during the IOP (00, 06, 12, 18 UTC). UCAR/JOSS conducted no quality control on these data. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude taken at a variable vertical resolution. Refer to the station README file for details. NOTE: This dataset has been updated (4/30/2002) with corrected data for the humidty measurement errors of the Vaisala RS 80 radiosonde (Wang et al 2002). Please see the README for details.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Impactor (2-stage) Data (Quinn)
summary: This dataset consists of 2-stage Impactor Data collected aboard the R/V Discoverer by P. Quinn (NOAA/PMEL) during ACE-1. Ion concentrations are given in ng/m3. Submicron values represent the ion concentration in all particles with aerodynamic diameters < 1.0 microns. Super micron values are for particles with aerodynamic diameters > 1 micron and < 10 microns. Diameters are given for the relative humidity of the sampled air stream. These diameters are given for a flow rate of 30 lpm and are subject to change after calibration of the collection efficiency of the impactor jet plate. This calibration is planned for the Fall, 1996.  Uncertainties associated with the ion concentrations range from +/- 5 to 25%. Please refer to the readme" file for a complete list of parameters and ions in this dataset."

title: SCICEX Hydrographic Data, 1997 and 1998
summary:
The Scientific Ice Expeditions (SCICEX) Program was a series of five multidisciplinary scientific cruises that utilized US Navy operational submarines as platforms for sampling the Arctic Ocean. The program's numerous principal investigators worked towards the overarching goal of characterizing the upper layers of the Arctic Ocean as completely as possible.

This data set includes hydrographic data obtained during the 1997 and 1998 (third and fourth) SCICEX cruises, aboard the USS Archerfish and the USS Hawkbill, respectively. Water column profile data were collected using a submarine-launched conductivity, temperature, and depth (CTD) probe. Probe depths were computed based on a known fall rate, temperature (T) and conductivity values were measured by probe sensors, and salinity was computed from these values. Derived variables, including pressure (calculated from depth and latitude), potential temperature, sigma-t (a representation of density), and sigma-theta (sigma-t calculated with potential temperature), are also included.

Profile data were generally collected to a depth of 1000 m at 1-m depth intervals, with variable horizontal distance between the profiles. Data were collected between September 3 and October 2, 1997, and between August 1 and September 2, 1998, along extensive transects within the Arctic Ocean.

title: Water Vapor Sensing System (Winds, Temperatures, and Water Vapor Fields from Commercial Aircraft) [NCAR/EOL]
summary: This data set contains the JOSS quality controlled WVSS-I data. This data has consistent water vapor information (dewpoint, RH, and mixing ratio are consistent), and has the benefit of time continuity to check for changes in WVSS-I calibration. IMPORTANT NOTE: The sensor technology of the first generation Water Vapor Sensing System (WVSS-I) is Vaisala's thin-film capacitor. Though a better sensor than found on radiosondes, it still loses calibration over time. The data from WVSS-I gathered from July 1, 1999 to December 31, 1999 has been evaluated and a scientific article is being prepared. This data is useful with data from four of the six aircraft considered quite good. One aircraft (#376) appears approximately 5% too wet and one aircraft (#441) appears approximately 5% too dry (very dry in November and December 1999). See the README for further information.

title: DOD Satellite Data
summary:
Satellite images archived in KuDA are derived from either the NOAA or the Dept of Defense polar orbiting weather satellites. This dataset contains images that are derived from the Department of Defense's polar orbiting weather satellites. The Department of Defense's DMSP (Defense Meteorological Satellite Program) had three satellites transmitting during 1991 (F8, F9, & F10). These satellites carry a sensor called the Operational Line Scanner (OLS) which is the one source of images for KuDA (the other source of images is NOAA's AVHRR). The OLS is a two-channel sensor with a broadband visible channel and an IR channel.

Data are in TDF and .TAR format.

title: When the Weather is Uggianaqtuq: Inuit Observations of Environmental Change
summary:
Uggianaqtuq (pronounced OOG-gi-a-nak-took ) is a North Baffin Inuktitut word that means to behave unexpectedly, or in an unfamiliar way. From the perspective of many hunters and elders in the Arctic, the weather has been uggianaqtuq in recent years. Inuit from two communities in Nunavut, Canada (Baker Lake and Clyde River), share their observations and perspectives on recent environmental changes. The CD-ROM is a pilot project that uses media technology, as opposed to written reports, as an alternative way to document and communicate Inuit observations and knowledge. It is a research product/report for the communities involved, as well as others interested in how Inuit are experiencing environmental change. Maps, text, photos, video and music are integrated to help illustrate the changes Inuit have observed in their environment and the impacts on their livelihoods. The integrated components allow the user to

* search by topic or the person being interviewed

* view interview clips in Inuktitut with English interpretations

* view and print maps about environmental changes drawn by participants

* view short videos with scenes from the communities

* view summaries and photos of environmental changes and their impacts to the landscape and community life.

The research project was funded by the National Science Foundation (NSF), grant number OPP-9906740, a doctoral fellowship from the Social Sciences and Humanities Research Council of Canada (SSHRC), and an award from the Innovative Research Program at the Cooperative Institute for Research in Environmental Sciences (CIRES), University of Colorado at Boulder (CU).

title: MARCUS RSV Aurora Australis Stabilized Platform Data
summary: This dataset contains a link to the MARCUS (Measurements of Aerosols, Radiation, and Clouds over the Southern Ocean) RSV Aurora Australis Stabilized Platform (S-TABLE) data in the DOE ARM Data Archive. You must have an ARM Archive account to access the data.

title: NASA Aura Satellite Ozone Monitoring Instrument (OMI) Level-2 Orbital Swath Data [NASA]
summary: The Ozone Monitoring Instrument (OMI) flies on NASA's Aura satellite, (launched on 15 July 2004). The Aura satellite is focused on observing atmospheric chemistry. This dataset contains Level-2 Orbital Swath Data (Nadir pixels 13x24 km) in HDF5 format

title: COMET CASE 004 WSR-88D Storm Total Precipitation Estimate from Kansas City, MO (EAX)
summary: This dataset contains the Storm Total Precipitation Estimate data product archived from the Kansas City, MO (EAX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: NEXRAD MPX (Minneapolis, MN) Reflectivity and Velocity Imagery
summary: This dataset includes NEXRAD Reflectivity and Velocity Imagery from the VORTEX2 field catalogs for 2009 and 2010. These imagery products are taken from the NEXRAD station located in Minneapolis, MN. The files are in .gif format.  Imagery files are only available for the VORTEX2 field phases for approximately May-June 2009 and April-June 2010. See the related links below to access the field catalogs for the exact time periods covered by this data set.

title: Belize City, Belize Rawinsonde Data
summary: This data set includes 140 high vertical resolution (2 second) soundings from the Belize City site in Belize (WMO 78583).  Soundings were typically released once per day (1200 UTC) from 1 June to 13 July 2004 and twice per day from 14 July to 2 September 2004.  The sites antenna failed on 3 September 2004 so no soundings are available for the remainder of the NAME period.

title: COMET CASE 024 NCEP's Nested Gridded Model (NGM).
summary: This dataset contains data from  NCEP's Nested Gridded Model (NGM). The model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecasts given every six hours going out 48 hours .  The data are archived in GRIB gridded files.

title: NWS Cooperative Observer and First Order Station Daily Snow Depth Data [NCDC]
summary: This data set contains daily snow depth observations for the National Weather Service Cooperative Observer network and First Order stations across the United States. The data are in a columnar ASCII format and were made available by NCDC. Data are only included for the two PLOWS field phases (February and March 2009 and November 2009 though March 2010. No data are included for the period between the field phases.

title: BASIS Fish Catch per Unit Effort (CPUE)
summary: Surface Fish tows collected in conjunction with Bering Arctic Subarctic Integrated Surveys (BASIS) Conductivity, temperature, and depth (CTD) profile data in the eastern Bering Sea. Note: data set is not continuous from Aug 2003- Sept. 2014.

title: High Rate (HRT - 25 sps) Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics Flight-Level Data
summary: This dataset includes airborne measurements obtained from the NSF/NCAR GV HIAPER (Gulfstream-V High-performance Instrumented Airborne Platform for Environmental Research) (N677F) during the CSET (Cloud System Evolution in the Trades) project. This dataset contains high rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in netCDF format.

title: Submicron Aerosol Teflon Filter Data Chand/Univ. of Washington
summary: This data set was collected during the VAMOLS Ocean-Cloud Atmosphere-Land Study-Regional Experiment (VOCALS-REx) from the Paposo upper site on the Chilean coast. The data are contained in a single EXCEL file.

title: HX-235 ADCP Data [Woodgate, R.]
summary: This is edited ship's Acoustic Doppler Current Profiler (ADCP) and Sea Surface (SS) underway data from the Alpha Helix mooring recovery and redeployment cruise August and September 2000. Data processed by Seth Danielson, University of Alaska Fairbanks (UAF). ADCP data quality control (QC) is described in the documentation. SS data have been only minimally cleaned up. Unedited underway data are available elsewhere in this archive.

title: S-Pol Radar, experimental refractivity product, DORADE format
summary: This dataset contains the S-band Polarimetric (S-Pol) experimental refractivity product in the Doppler Radar Data Exchange (DORADE) format, from the Terrain-influenced Monsoon Rainfall Experiment (TiMREX). Due to the size of the dataset, it is recommended that the user restrict data orders to several hours at a time per order ( .5 GB per 6 hour tar file). This data set is an experimental data set. Tammy Weckwerth should be consulted for details concerning this data set.

title: CloudSat Imagery
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: FASTEX soundings from the USAF C-130 dropsondes
summary: This dataset consists of dropsonde data from the USAF C-130.  Dropsondes were taken as requested.  These data were processed through automated and visual quality control.  These data include pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude taken at 10 second vertical intervals.  Refer to the station README for details.

title: HIPPO-4 Multiple Enclosure Device for Unfractionated Sampling of Air (MEDUSA) Kernel Data
summary: This dataset contains Multiple Enclosure Device for Unfractionated Sampling of Air (MEDUSA) kernel data collected by the NCAR GV during HIPPO-4. The data are in NASA Ames format. In order to compare in situ and flask values, an averaging kernel which takes into account flow rate and mixing time, tau, at time of sampling is required.

title: NCAR Homestead Site (ISS1) Real-time Plots
summary: This dataset provides a link to the NCAR/EOL archive of real time imagery from the ISS that was located at the SAVANT Homestead site.

title: Peroxy acetyl nitrate measurements during OASIS Barrow field intensive Spring 2009
summary: A measurement intensive campaign was carried out in Barrow, Alaska in spring 2009 as part of the Ocean-Atmosphere-Sea-Ice-Snowpack program. This dataset contains Peroxy Acetyl Nitrate (PAN) measurements using a Chemical Ionization Mass Spectrometer (CIMS).

title: GOES-8 Cloud Product Imagery
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: Skew-T Plots: Barrow
summary: This dataset contains upper air Skew-T Log-P data collected at Barrow, Alaska during the HIPPO project. The imagery are in GIF format. The imagery cover the time span from 2009-01-06 00:00:00 to 2009-02-01 12:00:00.

title: CACTI G1 Scanning Mobility Particle Sizer (SMPS) Campaign Data
summary: This dataset contains a link to the DOE ARM Archive G1 Scanning Mobility Particle Sizer (SMPS) campaign data. You must have an ARM Archive account to access these data.

title: Weekly Ice Analysis - Beaufort Sea [NIC]
summary: This dataset consists of the ice analysis performed by the National Naval Ice Center of the Beaufort Sea for the SBI field project. Images are in .jpg format.

title: NCEP Precipitation Analysis Imagery
summary: This dataset provides a link to the SAS Field Catalog Operational Products section which includes NCEP Precipitation Analysis Imagery.

title: CAMP: Mongolia Soil Temperature and Soil Moisture Data Set
summary:
This data set contains the Coordinated Energy and Water Cycle Observation Project (CEOP) Enhanced Observing Period 3 (EOP-3) and 4 (EOP-4) CEOP Asia-Australia Monsoon Project (CAMP) Mongolia Soil Temperature and Soil Moisture Data Set. This data set contains data from sixteen stations in the CAMP reference site for the CEOP EOP-3 and EOP-4 time period. This dataset contains the entire EOP-3 and EOP-4 time period (i.e., 1 October 2002 through 31 December 2004).

This data set contains both ASCII data and netCDF data. The ASCII data file covers the entire time period for all stations. The netCDF data file covers the entire time period with one netCDF file for each station.

title: COMET CASE 001 WSR-88D One-hour Precipitation Estimate from Melbourne, FL (MLB)
summary: This dataset contains the One-hour Precipitation Estimate  data product archived from the Melbourne, VA (LWX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: R/V Mirai Air-Sea Eddy Flux Data
summary: This dataset provides a link to the JAMSTEC CINDY data archive R/V Mirai eddy flux data.

title: Texas ET Network
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: Mobile GPS Radiosonde Data from CSU (ESC Format)
summary: Colorado State University (CSU) operated a mobile radiosonde system during the Mesoscale Predictability Experiment (MPEX) during the period from 10 May to 14 June 2013. Soundings were taken intermittently as determined by the weather situation, with a focus on the pre-convective and convectively disturbed environments near deep convective storms in the central United States. Soundings were coordinated with releases from the mobile teams from Purdue University and the National Severe Storms Laboratory (NSSL). This data set includes a total of 55 quality controlled, high vertical resolution (2 second) soundings are contained in the final MPEX data set.

title: HLY-02-03 Phytoplankton ID (Excel) [Grebmeier, J.]
summary: Phytoplankton with cell size larger than 2-3 microns were analyzed for taxonomic composition, size composition including colonies size, numbers and biomass and vertical distribution of all the parameters. Phytoplankton cell count samples were collected from the surface and the subsurface chlorophyll maximum at experimental and optical stations during the United States Coast Guard Cutter (USCGC) Healy SBI 2002 summer cruise (HLY0203). These data are in Excel format.

title: U. of Warsaw 10-hz Ultra Fast Thermometer (UFT) hot-wire temperature - NASA Ames format [Szymon Malinowski]
summary: This data set contains UFT data obtained during the Physics of Stratocumulus Tops"(POST) project off the west coast of Monterey
archive_note: CA. This data set contains 10 hertz UFT data. The files are in NASA Ames format."

title: ACE-1: Discoverer ISS High Vertical Resolution Balloon Data
summary: Data from the NCAR/Integrated Sounding System (ISS) upper air data collected aboard the ship R/V Discoverer during the ACE-1 transect and intensive operations, via the NCAR/Atmospheric Technology Division (ATD).  Data consist of 10-sec vertical resolution data (temperature, dew point temperature, pressure, and winds). These soundings were typically taken at 00 and 12 UTC daily with up to 6-hr frequency during intensive operations.

title: COMET CASE 018 WSR-88D Storm Relative Velocity (third-lowest tilt angle) from N. CENTRAL LOWER MICH
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Storm Relative Velocity (third-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  NORTH CENTRAL LOWER MICHIGAN (APX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: COMET CASE 043 composite reflectivity, 16 levels, 125 nmi range from DODGE CITY, KS/Dodge City
summary: This dataset contains the  composite reflectivity, 16 levels, 125 nmi range data product archived from the  DODGE CITY, KS/Dodge City (DDC) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: COMET CASE 032 NCEP's Eta Model.
summary: This dataset contains data from  NCEP's Eta Model. Model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecast times every six hours from 00 to 48 hours..  The data are archived in GRIB gridded files.

title: COMET CASE 018 GOES_9 IR3 at 8km
summary: This dataset contains GOES_9 IR3 imagery at 8km resolution. Data is archived as McIDAS AREA files.

title: NOAA R/V Ron Brown Stratus 9/VOCALS Cruise Technical Report [Whelan/WHOI]
summary: This dataset contains the Stratus 9/VOCALS Ninth Setting of the Stratus Ocean Reference Station & VOCALS Regional Experiment Technical Report
archive_note: Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution, Woods Hole, Massachusetts, April 2009.

title: GOES-10 4km Res Channel4 - Channel 2 Difference Imagery
summary: This dataset contains GOES-10 satellite imagery for the VOCALS study area and time of interest.  The images are JPEGS.

title: Dugway Proving Grounds Ceilometer Data at Baker, Delta and Tower Grid Sites
summary: This dataset contains the ceilometer data from the Dugway Proving Grounds measured at the Baker, Delta and Tower Grid sites in Utah collected during the Mountain Terrain Atmospheric Modeling and Observations Field Experimental Component (MATERHORN-X) campaign. The Baker and Delta sites' data collection occurred from 24 April 2013 to 5 June 2014, and the Tower Grid site collection lasted from 24 April 2013 to 26 May 2013. Files are the original data and have not been quality controlled. The file format is .txt, and the files been compressed and provided as zip files. Please refer to the readme for more information.

title: COMET CASE 029 Ship and Buoy Observations
summary: This dataset contains ship and buoy observation data in GEMPAK formatted files. There is one file per day containing data for every sixth hour  of the day.

title: CaPE Universityof Wyoming King Air Data
summary: The University of Wyoming Beechcraft King Air Super 200 was available from 15 July - 11 August 1991. Data consists of housekeeping and state parameters, particle spectra, liquid water content and forward video tapes (all at 1 second temporal resolution).

title: WRF 1KM Mixing Ratio Forecast Imagery (Rifle to Greeley) [Dudhia (NCAR-MMM)]
summary: This dataset contains Weather Research and Forecasting Model (WRF) 1 kilometer vertical cross-sections of four different mixing ratios, ice number concentration, and temperature. The imagery contains cloud water, rain water, snow, and Graupel mixing ratios. The imagery was generated from Rifle, CO to Greeley, CO during the ICE-L project. It is available in PNG format and covers the time span from 2007-11-19 00:00:00 to 2007-12-21 23:59:59.

title: COMET CASE 020 WSR-88D Base Reflectivity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) from WASHINGTON,DC
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Base Reflectivity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  WASHINGTON,DC (LWX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: COMET CASE 023 GOES_10 VIS at 4km_RAM
summary: This dataset contains GOES_10 VIS imagery at 4km_RAM resolution. Data is archived as McIDAS AREA files.

title: DTU WindScanner Lidar Ridge Scan Data in NetCDF format
summary: This data set contains the ridge scan data from four of the WindScanner Doppler lidars that were operated by DTU along the Perdigao ridges in Portugal. These data are in NetCDF format.

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Surface: Shortwave and Longwave Radiation Composite
summary: ARM SGP SIROS data, ARM SGP SIRS data, ARM SGP BSRN data, ARM SGP 25m MFR data, and HPCN data have been composited together into one data set. This data set is composed of 30-minute averages of observations taken either at 20 seconds (SIROS, SIRS and MFR) or 60 seconds (BSRN); or hourly data (HPCN). The SIROS and SIRS data contains observations of Upwelling and Downwelling Longwave and Shortwave Irradiance. The BSRN data has Downwelling Longwave and Shortwave; the MFR network contains Upwelling Longwave and Shortwave Irradiance; and the HPCN contains solar radiation equivalent to Downwelling Shortwave. These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: Soil Temperatures, Toolik Lake, Alaska, 1995 and 1996
summary: Soil temperatures were measured at the Toolik Lake Field Station during the summers of 1995 and 1996. Measurements were made on control plots, plots from which snow was removed, and plots from which snow was removed before the installation of heating cables at 10-cm depth. Plots with heating cables were heated two hours per day. Soil temperatures were recorded once per minute using a Campbell 21X micrologger measuring a thermocouple located at 5-cm soil depth in an intertussock area within each plot. Data are available in ASCII and MS Excel formats.

title: Atqasuk LAI Measurements (ASCII) [Walker, D.]
summary: This dataset contains leaf area index (LAI) measurements taken at peak biomass at the Atqasuk site on the Arctic Slope of Alaska, for the Arctic Transitions in the Land-Atmosphere System (ATLAS) project. The data were collected in 1999 and are in ASCII format. See the README for additional information.

title: GCIP/ESOP-96 Ancillary: Station List
summary: This dataset contains a list of stations whose data are included in the GCIP/ESOP-96 data sets. This list includes station name, latitude, longitude, elevation, station type, observing network ID, and station id.

title: Low Rate (LRT - 1 sps) Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics Flight-Level Data
summary:
This dataset includes airborne measurements obtained from the Gulfstream-V High-performance Instrumented Airborne Platform for Environmental Research (NSF/NCAR HIAPER) aircraft (Tail Number N677F) during the CONvective TRansport of Active Species in the Tropics (CONTRAST) project. This dataset contains low rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in netCDF format.

As of March 3, 2016, this dataset contains updated Ultra High Sensitvity Aerosol Spectrometer (UHSAS) data that corrects underestimated ambient concentrations.

title: WRF 4KM Equivalent Potential Temperature Forecast Imagery (Rock Springs to Ogallala) [Dudhia (NCAR-MMM)]
summary: This dataset contains Weather Research and Forecasting Model (WRF) 4 kilometer vertical cross-sections of Theta-E (Equivalent Potential Temperature). The imagery was generated from Rock Springs, WY to Ogallala, NE during the ICE-L project. It is available in PNG format and covers the time span from 2007-11-19 00:00:00 to 2007-12-21 23:59:59.

title: Right-Looking Digital Camera Imagery
summary: During SOCRATES-TEST, the NSF/NCAR HIAPER GV (Tail Number N677F) flew a right looking digital camera for in-flight video capture. Individual photo jpeg images were captured once per second during flights. Images taken after dark have been stripped from this archive. The remaining images have been combined into hour long tarfiles running from zero minutes zero seconds (or the start time of the first file) to 23 minutes 59 seconds (or the end time of the last file) after each hour. Note that the first and last tarfile for each flight will contain less than a full hour of imagery. Directory files returned with each order give the contents of each corresponding tar file.

title: PRELIMINARY Low Rate (LRT - 1 sps) Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics Flight-Level Data
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the NSF/NCAR C-130 aircraft (Tail Number N130AR) during the WE-CAN_2017 project. This dataset contains low rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in netCDF format. These are PRELIMINARY FIELD-PHASE data and are not for publication. Final, production data (with calibrated values in engineering units) having the highest-quality that RAF can provide will be available within 6 months of the end of the project.

title: COMET CASE 018 WSR-88D Storm Relative Velocity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) from MINNEAPOLIS, MN
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Storm Relative Velocity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  MINNEAPOLIS, MN/Chanhassen (MPX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: Gan, Addu Atoll, Maldives AMF-2 Surface Meteorology Data
summary: This data set contains the 1 minute surface meteorological data from the Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Mobile Facility (AMF) surface meteorological station was located on Gan during DYNAMO. The data are in NetCDF format.

title: COMET CASE 013 Ship and Buoy Observations
summary: This dataset contains ship and buoy observation data in GEMPAK formatted files.  There is one file per day containing data for every sixth hour of the day.

title: COMET CASE 003 WSR-88D Echo Tops from Tampa Bay, FL (TBW)
summary: This dataset contains the Echo Tops data product archived from the Tampa Bay, FL (TBW) radar.  Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: PMS-2D Two-dimensional Cloud Probe data [NCAR/EOL]
summary: This dataset contains raw (binary "filmstrip" imagery) files of PMS-2D data collected by the C-130 during the Instrument Development and Education in Airborne Science Phase 3 (IDEAS-3) project which took place from 15 August 2003 to 22 September 2003. These data are in a format compatible with xpms2d, available from the EOL xpms2d download page. Click on "Order" to see a table listing flight dates and times during which data is available.

title: DC-8 Scanning High-resolution Interferometer Sounder (S-HIS)
summary: This dataset provides a link to the University of Wisconsin DC-8 Scanning High-resolution Interferometer Sounder (S-HIS) IHOP information website.

title: Lake-ICE Surface: MAPS Analysis (T,dew point,P,P tendency) (GIF)
summary: US MAPS surface analysis provided every 3 hours. 4-Panel plot includes temperature, dew point, pressure and pressure tendency. Images taken from NCAR/RAP site generated at NMC.

title: ARSV L.M. Gould Atmospheric O2 / CO2 Data
summary: This dataset provides a link to R/V L. M. Gould Atmospheric O2 / CO2 Data Processing Page.

title: P-3 CNRS Leandre II Imagery [NCAR/EOL]
summary: This dataset contains CNRS Leandre II imagery from data recorded during P-3 flights. The images are at 15-20 minute intervals. Each interval contains a backscattering or raw signal image along with a water vapor mixing ratio image.

title: High Rate (HRT - 25 sps) Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics Flight-Level Data
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the NSF/NCAR C-130 aircraft (Tail Number N130AR) during the WINTER project. This dataset contains high rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in netCDF format.

title: ACE-ASIA Model: Meteorology ARL Trajectories; Back - Imagery (JOSS)
summary: The ACE-Asia Model Meteorology ARL Trajectories; Back - Imagery (JOSS) are available online. This data was collected during the ACE-Asia intesive observing period March 23, 2001 thru May 5, 2001.

title: CASA X-band Radar Network in SW Oklahoma
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: Quantum Cascade Laser Spectrometer CO2 [Wofsy (Harvard)]
summary: The Quantum Cascade Laser Spectrometer CO2 measured CO2 concentrations in situ aboard the NSF/NCAR GV during HIPPO-4. This dataset contains CO2_QCLS data in NASA Ames format collected during HIPPO-4.

title: Outgoing Longwave Radiation and Highly Reflective Clouds Datasets at SUNY (Stony Brook)
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: Cayenne STARNET Lightning Data (kml)
summary: This dataset contains Sferics Timing and Ranging Network (STARNET) long-range lightning detection data from the High Altitude Ice Crystals - High Ice Water Content (HAIC-HIWC) project that took place in Cayenne, French Guiana. The STARNET lightning detection network is run by the University of Sao Paulo, Brazil at the Laboratorio de Sensoriamento Remoto de Tempestades (STORM-T), Department of Atmospheric Sciences, IAG. The data files were processed by the National Center for Atmospheric Research (NCAR) Earth Observing Laboratory (EOL) and are in .kml (Google Earth) file format.

title: ARL Scintillometer Data
summary: This data set contains the raw, preliminary data from the Army Research Laboratory (ARL) Scintec BLS450 Scintillometer during the Perdigao field season. The antenna was located at the George" site and the receiver at the "Lionstail" site. These data are in an ASCII format. Due to a recording issue
archive_note:
data are only available for 5-7 May 2017.

"

title: Boston University All-Sky Imager Data Archives
summary: Boston University Imaging Science Laboratory (ISL) employs all-sky imagers for their terrestrial atmospheric studies. The Related Links section points to the Boston University All-Sky Imager Data Archives. Learn more about this dataset at http://sirius.bu.edu/intro/.
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: ACE-ASIA Surface: China Hefei Aerosol Elemental Composition 8-Stage Drum Impactor (Cahill)
summary: This dataset contains size-resolved aerosol elemental composition measurements with 3-hour resolution collected at the Anhui Institute of Optics and Fine Mechanics in Hefei, China.

title: Lake-ICE Surface: Specials Composite
summary: This dataset contains only the Lake-ICE Automated Surface Observing System (ASOS) and National Climatic Data Center (NCDC) DATSAV2 "Special" observation surface data for the Lake-ICE domain and time period. These are observations that are reported at off-hour times. The ASOS and DATSAV2 "Nominal" hourly surface data for the Lake-ICE domain and time period are included in the Lake-ICE Hourly Surface Composite.

title: Forward-looking Digital Camera Movies - preliminary
summary: During the Wintertime Investigation of Transport, Emission, and Reactivity (WINTER) project, the NSF/NCAR C-130 (Tail Number C130_N130AR) flew digital cameras for in-flight video capture. The original images are 1280x960 pixels and were recorded at 1 frame/second. Images taken after dark have been stripped from this archive. Remaining images were converted to Quicktime movie files. The movies are h.264 codec playable with Quicktime (Mac and Windows), xine, (linux) and mplayer (many platforms). The movies are set to play back at 640x480 pixels and 15 fps so the entire flight plays back in about 30 minutes. Fast-forward, reverse, scrubbing, etc. is possible in most players. Files are typically 300 MB in size. Preliminary movies were only created for the first 6 flights.

title: GOES 13 SouthEast 1KM Channel 1 Visible Imagery
summary: This dataset includes GOES 13 Southeast 1 km channel 1 visible imagery from the 2010 field phase of the VORTEX2 field catalog. The files are jpg images. See the catalog link in the related links section below to access the field catalog.

title: COMET CASE 002 WSR-88D Base Reflectivity (lowest tilt angle) from Cleveland, OH (CLE)
summary: This dataset contains the base reflectivity (lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the Cleveland, OH (CLE) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: Howard University High Resolution Soundings - Barbados (UWyo ASCII Format) [NCAR/EOL]
summary: This is one of the upper air data sets developed for the Pre-Depression Investigation of Cloud-systems in the Tropics (PREDICT) project. This data set includes 99 high vertical resolution (4 second) soundings from Barbados taken by Howard University from 14 August through 25 September 2010. The files in this dataset are in the University of Wyoming ASCII format.

title: NASA DC-8 Diode Laser Hygrometer (DLH) Water Vapor Mixing Ratio Measurements (TCIDC)
summary: A link is provided to the NASA LaRC Intercontinental Chemical Transport Experiment Phase B (INTEX-B) Data Archive NASA DC-8 Diode Laser Hygrometer (DLH) Water Vapor Mixing Ratio Measurements data  from Glenn Diskin.

title: NWS Cooperative Observer 15-minute Precipitation Data [NCDC]
summary: This data set contains 15-minute resolution precipitation data from the National Weather Service Cooperative Network. These stations are located across the BAMEX region. This data set covers the period from 20 May to 7 July 2003

title: UND Scanning Doppler Lidar at the MI6 Site
summary: This data set contains the raw, preliminary data from the University of Notre Dame Halo Scanning Doppler Lidar at the MI6" site during the Perdigao field season. These data are in the Halo ASCII format. These data are not available for direct ordering. Please contact Raghu Krishnamurthy (rkrishn1@nd.edu) for access to these data. A processed
archive_note:
quality controlled version is in development.

"

title: TAO buoys enhanced for PACS/EPIC
summary: A link is provided to the TAO/EPIC Project homepage.

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) WSI NIDS Layer Composite Reflectivity (24,000 to 33,000 feet) Valley, NE
summary: This dataset contains the Layer Composite Reflectivity at  the second level (24,000 to 33,000 feet) data product archived from the WSI NIDS datastream for the Valley, NE radar. Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format, at a frequency of 5 minutes.

title: SCanning Imaging Absorption SpectroMeter for Atmospheric CHartographY (SCIAMACHY)
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: NSF/NCAR C-130 Measurements of Peroxyacyl Nitrates (PANs) CIGARette (TCIDC)
summary: A link is provided to the NASA LaRC Intercontinental Chemical Transport Experiment Phase B (INTEX-B) Data Archive NSF/NCAR C-130 Measurements of Peroxyacyl Nitrates (PANs) CIGARette data  from Frank Flocke

title: GCIP/NESOB-96 Surface: Momentum Flux Data
summary: NOAA/ATDD Little Washita momentum flux data. This dataset is composed of half hourly observations of average wind vector speed, kinematic shear stress, streamwise velocity variance, crosswind velocity variance, and vertical velocity variance. These data were not quality checked by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: DMSP Data

title: Ivotuk Climate Data - MNT Site (ASCII) [Beringer, J.]
summary:
This dataset includes climate data from the MNT site near Ivotuk gathered during the 1998 summer field season. Surface energy and trace gas exchange measurements were made at each of the Ivotuk sites using the eddy covariance technique. The MAT site was operated continuously over the growing season whilst the remaining sites were characterized by a single tower that was moved from site to site. The MAT site is therefore used as a reference.

This dataset is available in both ASCII and EXCEL formats - For data browsing, we suggest ordering the EXCEL version and using EXCEL to plot the data. NOTE: This dataset contains the data in ASCII format.

This presentation is part of the Bering Sea Ecosystem Study-Bering Sea Integrated Ecosystem Research Program (BEST-BSIERP). BEST-BSIERP together are the Bering Sea project.

title: HLY-09-01 TeraScan Raw DMSP Satellite Data [Cooper, L./LDEO]
summary: This dataset includes raw data from the SeaSpace TeraScan System. The data are from the F13, F14, F15, F16 and F17 Defense Meteorological Satellites Program (DMSP) satellites. The data are from the satellite passes that occurred over the Bering Sea during the Bering Sea Ecosystem Study-Bering Sea Integrated Ecosystem Research Program (BEST-BSIERP) 2009 0901 (early spring) cruise onboard the U.S. Coast Guard Cutter Healy. BEST-BSIERP together are the Bering Sea project. The individual data files have been collected into tar files by day.

title: HLY-04-02 Benthic Station Data (benthic faunal data and sediment tracers) (ASCII) [Grebmeier, J. and L. Cooper]
summary: This data set contains measurements of benthic parameters, including bottom water temperature and salinity, bottom water chlorophyll-a concentrations, integrated water column chlorophyll-a, sediment chlorophyll-a present in surface sediments, benthic faunal parameters (abundance, biomass (g/m2), biomass (gC/m2), number of taxa), sediment grain size, total organic carbon (TOC), total organic nitrogen (TON), carbon/nitrogen (C/N), and sediment respiration oxygen uptake rates (O2UR). Data included in this dataset were collected during sampling from May 15. 2004 to June 23, 2004 from the U.S. Coast Guard Cutter (USCGC) Healy (WAGB-20). This sampling on Healy was funded through the Shelf-Basin Interactions SBI)project, which is funded by both the National Science Foundation and the Office of Naval Research. These data are in ASCII format.

title: NDTP: PAM-II Data [CMF]
summary: This data set is a single tar file containing cmf text files of PAM station data from the North Dakota Thunderstorm Project (NDTP).

title: GTS Mandatory/Significant Level Sounding Data (EOL Format)
summary: National weather agencies around the world routinely release radiosondes at 00 and/or 12 UTC with occasional special releases. This data set includes the quality controlled Tropical Cyclone Intensity (TCI)  Global Telecommunication System (GTS) soundings released at sites near the locations of TCI flown tropical cyclones. TCI flew two storms in the Atlantic (Erika and Joaquin) and two storms in the eastern Pacific basin (Marty and Patricia). For Erika, this data set includes soundings from 25-30 August 2015 from Cape Canaveral, Nassau, Kingston, Grand Cayman, Saint Maarten, and Guadeloupe. For Joaquin, the included soundings are from 25 September to 6 October 2015 from Bermuda, Cape Canaveral, Nassau, Kingston, Grand Cayman, and Saint Maarten. For Patricia, the included soundings are from 19-24 October 2015 from Monterrey, Guadalupe, Guadalajara, Manzanillo, Mexico City, Acapulco, La Paz, Mazatlan, and Veracruz. For Marty the included soundings are from 25 September to 1 October 2015 from Guadalupe, Guadalajara, Manzanillo, Mexico City, and Acapulco. A total of 349 quality-controlled, mandatory and significant level resolution soundings are contained in the final TCI data set.
archive_note: On 2/6/2019, new soundings were added to this dataset to cover the time period when the High Ice Water Content (HIWC) Radar Study project was operating out of Fort Lauderdale, Florida. The 238 new soundings are from 8/9/2015 through 8/24/2015.

title: OU/NSSL CLAMPS AERIoe Temperature and Water Vapor Profile Data
summary: This data set contains temperature and water vapor mixing ratio profiles along with cloud properties for a single layer cloud (i.e., liquid water path and effective radius) data from the AERI (Atmospheric Emitted Radiance Interferometer) that was onboard the OU/NSSL CLAMPS vehicle that was deployed at Belle Mina, Alabama during the VORTEX-SE 2016 field campaign. These data are in NetCDF format. These data were processed using release 2.2 of the AERIoe algorithm. Also included are daily quicklook browse imagery.

title: Soundings, Ice Camp NCAR/GLAS raobs. (ASCII) [Moritz, R.]

One-second time resolution ASCII data are provided for each launch time at 0000 and 1200 UTC daily. JPEG skew-t plots are also available. (13.201) This data has had some quality control.

title: NASA DC-8 LARGE UHSAS PSL Data

This data set is in ICARTT format. Please see the header portion of the data files for details on instruments, parameters, quality assurance, quality control, contact information, and data set comments.

title: NCAR MISS 915 MHz DBS Wind Profiler Data [NCAR/EOL]
summary:
NCAR/EOL operated three 915 MHz boundary layer wind profiler radars at ISS (Integrated Sounding System) sites at T-REX. These radars detect scattering from clear-air refractivity gradients (such as those due to turbulence and inversions) and from precipitation. Two of the three wind profilers were standard DBS (Doppler Beam Swinging) systems, one of which provided the data for the accompanying data set. The DBS profilers at T-REX were designated ISS2 and MISS and produced wind measurements every 30 minutes and also made a 5-minute RASS profile at 30-minute intervals.

This dataset includes MISS winds, moments, and rass data. The MISS system was a mobile system and moved around 5 sites in the Owens Valley.

title: ArcticRIMS: Daily Precipitation From Statistical Reconstructions
summary:
Providing rapid updates of gridded precipitation fields is difficult due to the degradation of the station network. Starting about 1990, many stations in the Former Soviet Union (FSU) and Canada closed. Canada is also seeing a trend toward automation. In recognition, we are providing updated fields using statistical techniques. This reconstruction technique has also been used to compile fields back to 1980 to provide a period of overlap with gridded fields based on interpolation of monthly station precipitation and daily disaggregation (see DAILY PRECIPITATION, FROM MONTHLY STATION RECORDS AND DISAGGREGATION). The reconstructions employ a four-step approach. As part of the data processing of ArcticRIMS (http://RIMS.unh.edu) based at the Water Systems Analysis Group, University of New Hampshire all data sets have been aggregated to multiple temporal and spatial resolutions.

The data is presented in 24 sub-datasets of different spatial and temporal aggregations.

title: Downward-Looking Digital Camera Imagery
summary: During ARISTO2015, the NSF/NCAR C-130 (Tail Number C130_N130AR) flew a downward looking digital camera for in-flight video capture. Individual photo jpeg images were captured once per second during flights. Images taken after dark have been stripped from this archive. The remaining images have been combined into hour long tarfiles running from zero minutes zero seconds (or the start time of the first file) to 23 minutes 59 seconds (or the end time of the last file) after each hour. Note that the first and last tarfile for each flight will contain less than a full hour of imagery. Directory files returned with each order give the contents of each corresponding tar file.

title: HIPPO-4 Multiple Enclosure Device for Unfractionated Sampling of Air (MEDUSA) Flask Data
summary: The Multiple Enclosure Device for Unfractionated Sampling of Air (MEDUSA) flask data contains measurements of O2, CO2, Ar/N2 13CO2, and C18O16O. The data were collected by the NCAR GV during HIPPO-4. The data are in NASA Ames format.

summary: This data set contains Particulate Organic Carbon and Particulate Organic Nitrogen data for the United States Coast Guard Cutter (USCGC) Healy HLY-02-03 Cruise. The summer cruise spanned 18 July 2002 to 21 August 2002.

title: GPS data

The GFZ German Research Centre for Geosciences in Potsdam, Germany processed the data to provide precipitable water vapor (PWV) fields.

title: SMART-R Radar Rain Rate Data: DYNAMO Legacy Collection
summary: This data set contains the 10 minute resolution gridded rain rate data from the SMART-R1 Doppler radar that was located on Addu Atoll of the Maldive Islands during DYNAMO. The data are in NetCDF format.

title: NASA DC-8 WAS Data Merge
summary: This data set contains NASA DC-8 WAS Data Merge data collected during the Deep Convective Clouds and Chemistry Experiment (DC3) from 18 May 2012 through 22 June 2012. These are updated merges from the NASA DC3 archive. In most cases, variable names have been kept identical to those submitted in the raw data files. However, in some cases, names have been changed (e.g., to eliminate duplication). Units have been standardized throughout the merge. In addition, a grand merge" has been provided. This includes data from all the individual merged flights throughout the mission. This grand merge will follow the following naming convention: "dc3-mrgWAS-dc8_merge_YYYYMMdd_R5_thruYYYYMMdd.ict" (with the comment "_thruYYYYMMdd" indicating the last flight date included).

A bathymetry grid was interpolated from depth soundings measured in meters below mean lower low water (MLLW) and contours that were digitized from a National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) nautical chart (28 July 1990 1:47,943-scale, chart #16082). The data set includes the derived bathymetry grid, the depth soundings map, and the contour map.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer CO2 Measurements (Feely)

The air data are noisy, which happens when the air lines get filled with sea spray during bad weather. The water data look fine according to R. Feely.

This instrument is similar to that of Gerbig, et al.( Journal of Geophysical Research, Vol. 104, No. D1, 1699-1704, 1999). VOCALS data have a 3ppbv precision, 1-second resolution, and a typical accuracy of 3 ppbv +/- 5%. This is the netCDF-formatted version of the data.

summary:
This dataset includes climate data from the MAT site near Ivotuk gathered during the 1998 summer field season. Surface energy and trace gas exchange measurements were made at each of the Ivotuk sites using the eddy covariance technique. The MAT site was operated continuously over the growing season whilst the remaining sites were characterized by a single tower that was moved from site to site. The MAT site is therefore used as a reference.

This dataset is available in both ASCII and EXCEL formats - For data browsing, we suggest ordering the EXCEL version and using EXCEL to plot the data. NOTE: This dataset contains the data in ASCII format.
