summary: This data set contains PRELIMINARY quicklook imagery from the Wyoming Cloud Lidar on-board the NSF/NCAR C-130 during PLOWS 2009-2010. The products include power and depolarization. The imagery were developed by the University of Wyoming.

title: GCIP/EAOP-98 Surface: Hourly Surface Meteorological Composite
summary: The GCIP/EAOP-98 Hourly Surface Composite contains data from several networks (i.e., Automated Surface Observing System, Great Lakes Environmental Research Laboratory, National Climatic Data Center DATSAV3, University of Kentucky Research Farms, North Carolina Agricultural Research Service Weather and Climate Network, Illinois Climate Network, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration Atmospheric Turbulence and Diffusion Division, Natural Resource Conservation Service Soil Moisture Soil Temperature Network, USDA/ARS North Appalachian Experimental Watershed Data (Coshocton), Coweeta Long Term Ecological Research, W.K. Kellogg Biological Station, the Environmental Protection Agency, and the Tennessee Valley Authority) for the EAOP 98 LSA-East domain. Data from these sources were merged and quality controlled to form this Surface Composite.

title: COMET CASE 044 base reflectivity, 248 nmi range, 0.50 degree elevation angle from OHX
summary: This dataset contains the  base reflectivity, 248 nmi range, 0.50 degree elevation angle data product archived from the  NASHVILLE, TN/Old Hickory OHX radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: GOES-East 3-hourly 1km Visible Channel Area Files SE Pacific [NCAR/EOL]
summary: This dataset contains MCIDAS area files of GOES-8 Satellite data at 1 kilometer resolution. The data are tarred into dayfile. The data cover the period from 1 Sept - 23 Oct 2001 (2001d244-296)

title: High Plains Climate Network [HPCN]
summary: This data set contains the High Plains Climate Network (HPCN) hourly surface data for the VORTEX2 2009 and 2010 field phases for approximately May-June 2009 and May-June 2010.  Data are provided in month files by station for 125 stations within Colorado, Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Montana, Nebraska, North Dakota and South Dakota. The following parameters are included in these data: Air Temperature, Relative Humidity, Soil Temperature, Wind Speed, Wind Magnitude, Vect dir, Vect SD, Rad Flux, and Total precipitation. The data are provided as is" in their original format."

title: CACTI Aerodynamic Particle Sizer (APS) Data
summary: This dataset contains a link to the DOE ARM Archive CACTI Aerodynamic Particle Sizer (APS) data. You must have an ARM Archive account to access these data.

title: USGS Stream Flow Data [NCAR/EOL]
summary: The United States Geological Survey (USGS) stream flow dataset is one of various datasets provided for the North American Monsoon Experiment 2004 (NAME 2004). This dataset contains stream flow data from USGS stations in the NAME 2004 domain for the complete 2004 Water Year (1 October 2003 through 30 September 2004) including the NAME time period (1 June 2004 through 30 Sept 2004) for approximately 3068 stations. The NAME 2004 domain is approximately 90W to 120W longitude and 10N to 40N latitude (i.e., Tier 2). No additional quality control was performed by the National Center for Atmospheric Research/Earth Observing Laboratory (NCAR/EOL).

title: Arizona Meteorological Network (AZMET) Data
summary: This data set contains hourly resolution surface meteorological data from the Mesonet Arizona Meteorological Network (AZMET). There are 28 stations covered by this data set, located across the state of Arizona. This data set covers the period from 1 January 2004 to 31 December 2004. These data are in comma delimited ASCII format. NCAR/EOL has not done any processing or quality control on these data.

title: COMET CASE 043 Upperair Profiler Data
summary: This dataset contains upperair profiler observation data in GEMPAK formatted files.  There is one file per day containing hourly data for the day.

title: NASA DC-8 LARGE ABS Data
summary: This data set contains NASA DC-8 Langley Aerosol Research Group Experiment (LARGE) In-situ Aerosol Absorption (ABS) Data collected during the Deep Convective Clouds and Chemistry Experiment (DC3) from 18 May 2012 through 22 June 2012. This data set is in ICARTT format. Please see the header portion of the data files for details on instruments, parameters, quality assurance, quality control, contact information, and data set comments.

title: HLY-04-02 Particulate Organic Carbon (POC) and Particulate Nitrogen (PN) in sediments (Excel) [Harvey, R.]
summary: This data set represents measurements of particulate organic carbon (POC) and Particulate Nitrogen (PN) for water column suspended particles collected during the 2004 U.S. Coast Guard Cutter (USCGC) Healy HLY-04-02 Process Cruise. Particulates were collected by filtration onto pre-combusted (450C for 4hrs) 25mm Whatman GF/F filters. The filters were stored frozen until analysis. Filters were dried at 40C for 24 hours, then carbonates were removed by vapor phase acidification with HCl. Samples were analyzed at the Nutrient Analytical Services Laboratory at the Chesapeake Biological Laboratory, University of Maryland Center for Environmental Science, Solomons, Maryland, using an Exeter Analytical, Inc., CE-440 Elemental Analyzer. These data are in Excel format.

title: NASA DC-8 PANAK Oxygenated Volatile Organic Chemicals and Tracers Using the PANAK Instrument (TCIDC)
summary: A link is provided to the NASA LaRC Intercontinental Chemical Transport Experiment Phase B (INTEX-B) Data Archive NASA DC-8 PANAK Oxygenated Volatile Organic Chemicals and Tracers Using the PANAK Instrument data  from Hanwant Singh

title: NWS Cooperative Observer Daily Observations [NCDC]
summary: This data set contains daily meteorological data from the National Weather Service Cooperative Network. These stations are located across the T-REX region. This data set covers the period from 1 March to 30 April 2006.

title: HIAPER Atmospheric Radiation Package (HARP) CCD Actinic Flux Spectrometers Photolysis Frequencies [Hall, Schmidt (NCAR-ACD, CU-LASP)]
summary: This dataset contains photolysis frequencies calculated from spectrally resolved actinic flux measurements taken aboard the NCAR G-V as a part of HIAPER Atmospheric Radiation Package (HARP) during the TORERO project.

title: COMET CASE 005 WSI NIDS Storm Total Precipitation Estimate from Pittsburgh, PA
summary: This dataset contains the Storm Total Precipitation Estimate data product archived from the WSI NIDS datastream for the Pittsburgh, PA radar. Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format, at a frequency of 10 minutes.

title: UK BAE-146 Navigation, State Parameter, Microphysics, Aerosol, and Chemistry Data - 1Hz [UKMO]
summary:
This data set contains state parameter, microphysics and navigation data from the BAE-146 aircraft during the RICO project. The data are all 1 Hz averaged with the main data files in NetCDF format, with filenames in the form: RICO_FAAM_yyyymmdd_Rn_Bfff.NC where yyyymmdd is the flight date, n is a release number for the dataset (currently zero) and fff our own flight number (072 to 080 inclusive).

Each file is accompanied by a text file, RICO_FAAM_yyyymmdd_Rn_Bfff_DESCRIP.TXT which is an ascii text file giving details of the parameters included in the dataset and the data flagging scheme that we employ for quality control. Because of the way that data flags are employed, the NetCDF file contains for each parameter a further parameter which gives its flag values.

Since we are still investigating the calibration of some instruments and systems (in particular the windfinding system), this current dataset should be regarded as preliminary. Subsequent versions will have the release number updated.

title: COMET CASE 020 WSR-88D Storm Total Precipitation Estimate from RALEIGH, NC
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Storm Total Precipitation Estimate data product archived from the  RALEIGH, NC (RAX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: Pelagic distribution and abundance of seabirds in the PROBES area
summary:
This data set includes data from the PROBES area, gathered by multiple observers in multiple projects, since 1975. The data were gathered in strip transects, generally 300 m wide and recorded in the data base as densities. Over that period, there has been a change in the method for recording flying birds. Before the year 2000, most, if not all, data on flying birds were recorded continuously, which can result in an inflated number of birds recorded per unit area. After 2000, most flying birds were recorded with the snap-shot method. The data in this dataset were retrieved from the USGS maintained North Pacific Pelagic Seabird Database, version 2, which is expected to be on line by late 2014, which have not been adjusted for the change in recording methods. Such a calibration was made for the Hunt et al. in press paper listed below, and information on calibration methods are in that paper and in the Renner et al paper below in related links.

This data set is part of the Bering Sea Ecosystem Study-Bering Sea Integrated Ecosystem Research Program (BEST-BSIERP). BEST-BSIERP together are the Bering Sea project.

title: RSMAS CWRF 1.3km nest with JMA Initial Condition Forecast [RSMAS]
summary: This data set contains RSMAS CWRF model (using JMA initial boundary conditions) forecast imagery over the Western Pacific Ocean with the 1.3 km nest around the tropical cyclone. Products include rain rate and sea level pressure (large and storm scale), 500mb heights/winds, reflectivity at the storm scale, sea surface temperature and anomaly, 250-850mb wind shear, and surface winds (large and storm scale). Products are available during limited tropical cyclone cases every 6 hours to 72 hours. These images were developed by the University of Miami RSMAS and are in gif format.

title: ACE-ASIA Aircraft: C-130 High Rate (25 sps) Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics Flight-Level Data
summary: This dataset contains netCDF data obtained aboard the NCAR/NSF C-130 aircraft during the ACE-Asia project. This dataset contains the High Rate (HRT, 25 sps) Flight Level production data. HRT data is available for only six of the eighteen flights.

title: COMET CASE 043 storm relative mean radial v, 2.40 degrees ele from GOODLAND, KS/Goodland
summary: This dataset contains the  storm relative mean radial velocity, 2.40 degrees elevation angle (P) data product archived from the  GOODLAND, KS/Goodland (GLD) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics HRT Data in NetCDF format
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the NCAR Research Aviation Facility (RAF) King Air aircraft (Tail Number: N312D) during the Particulate Airborne Inlet Research (PAIR) project. This dataset contains high rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in NetCDF format.

title: NCAR/EOL Driftsonde Data
summary: Driftsonde sounding data for the THORPEX Pacific Asian Regional Campaign (T-PARC) project. The files are in EOL format, an ascii text format including a header and typically seventeen columns of high resolution data. See the Documentation for a more complete descrition of this data set.

title: VORTEX NOAA WP-3D Radar Data
summary: NOAA operated a WP-3D research aricraft during VORTEX. It carries 2 radars: A non-coherent horizontally scanning lower fuselage radar and a 3 cm wavelength vertically scanning tail Doppler radar. Both radars are three-axis stabilized.

title: Aircraft State Parameters Data
summary: This dataset contains Aircraft State Parameter data from the High Ice Water Content (HIWC) Radar Study project that took place in Fort Lauderdale, Florida. The data are from the NASA DC-8 aircraft from the 11 flights that were flown during the project and are in ICARTT format.

title: ACE-1: Discoverer Aerosol Size Distributions Data (Quinn)
summary: This dataset consists of Aerosol Size Distributions Data collected aboard the R/V Discoverer by P. Quinn (NOAA/PMEL) during ACE-1. The data are compiled in 30 minute averages from 15 minutes before to 15 minutes after the half hour.  The time is given as decimal day of year (JDAY).

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Upper Air: NWS and ARM 5 hPa Vertical Resolution Sounding Data Set
summary: The GCIP/NESOB-97 5 hPa ARM and NWS Soundings dataset contains 5 hPa interpolated sounding data extracted from 12 NWS sounding sites and five ARM sounding sites in the NESOB-97 domain. Only the data from the surface to 3000 m have been retained in this data set. The high resolution data were quality controlled with every sounding subjected to automated consistency checks. This dataset includes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude.See the readme for further information.

title: Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics LRT Data (Electra) in NetCDF format
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the NCAR Research Aviation Facility (RAF) Electra aircraft (Tail Number: N308D) during the Experiment on Rapidly-Intensifying Cyclones over the Atlantic (ERICA) project. This dataset contains low rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in NetCDF format.

title: Barrow Area Remote Sensing- BE CO2 Flux Summer 2009
summary:
This data set contains half-hourly vertical fluxes of CO2 and related environmental measurements taken at the Biocomplexity Experimental Site in northern Alaska during the summer of 2009. Sampling was conducted as part of a large-scale water manipulation experiment to test the effect of altered tundra moisture on ecosystem carbon exchange.

The variables measured were: CO2 flux H2O flux, latent and sensible heat fluxes, turbulence characteristics, radiation, meteorological variables, ground heat flux (5 replicates), and soil temperature (1 cm depth). Sample date and time are also given.

title: COMET CASE 018 WSR-88D Radial Velocity (third-lowest tilt angle) from DETROIT, MI
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Radial Velocity (third-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  DETROIT, MI/White Lake (DTX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: Oklahoma Lightning Mapping Array (OKLMA) Data
summary: This dataset contains Oklahoma Lightning Mapping Array (OKLMA) data. These data were collected from 19 May to 22 June 2012 as part of the Deep Convective Clouds and Chemistry (DC3) Project.

title: COMET CASE 022 GOES_8 IR4 at 2km
summary: This dataset contains GOES_8 IR4 imagery at 2km resolution.  Data is archived as McIDAS AREA files.

title: SOAS and SENEX NOAA Data (SENEX password required)
summary: This dataset provides a link to the NOAA SENEX/SOAS Data Archive website.

title: COMET CASE 016 WSR-88D Total Precipitation Estimate from St. Louis, MO (LSX)
summary: This dataset contains the Total Precipitation Estimate  data product archived from the St. Louis, MO (LSX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: Sagar Kanya Meteorology Rawinsonde Soundings [Heymsfield]
summary: This dataset consists of rawinsonde data collected during INDOEX from the Oceanographic Research Vessel (ORV) Sagar Kanya. Each datafile contains the ship's location, the sonde's UTC release time, and a vertical profile of pressure, temperature, humidity, latitude and longitude, total wind speed and direction, and U and V wind components, every 1 second during the sonde's ascent.

title: Sediment trap data of vertical flux of algal pigments, POC and PON
summary: This dataset contains data on vertical flux of algal pigments and particulate organic carbon and nitrogen determined by deploying sediment traps under sea ice in the Bering Sea in 2008, 2009, and 2010. After retrieval the samples were split for analysis of algal pigments. Data were collected during the Bering Sea Ecosystem Study-Bering Sea Integrated Ecosystem Research Program (BEST-BSIERP). BEST-BSIERP together are the Bering Sea project.

title: COMET CASE 030 WSR-88D Three-Hour Precipitation Estimate from DENVER/BOULDER, CO
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Three-Hour Precipitation Estimate data product archived from the  DENVER/BOULDER, CO (FTG) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: Land-Cover Map of the North Slope of Alaska
summary: This ArcInfo map provides a spatially explicit representation of the nature and distribution of land cover and tundra types on the North Slope of Alaska. This was done in support of extrapolating ecosystem models developed in the Kuparuk to the North Slope.

title: DOTSTAR ASTRA NCAR/EOL Dropsonde TEMPDROP Data
summary: TEMPDROP messages from the dropsondes released by the DOTSTAR ASTRA jet aircraft that flew during the ITOP field program. The DOTSTAR aircraft were based out of Taiwan and flew around tropical systems in the western Pacific Ocean during August-October 2010. The data files are in the GTS TEMPDROP format and contain the mandatory and significant level observations from the DOTSTAR dropsondes. NCAR/EOL have conducted no quality control on these data files.

title: COMET CASE 023 WSR-88D Radial Velocity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) from SPRINGFIELD, MO
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Radial Velocity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  SPRINGFIELD, MO (SGF) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: STORM-FEST Hourly Precipitation Composite
summary: Hourly composite containing data from all networks measuring precipitation during STORM-FEST (about 2700 sites). Data includes that collected from national, regional and special research network data sets. Limited quality control was performed on this dataset. See the "README" file for more details.

title: GAPP: Ft. Peck Flux Data Set
summary:
This data set contains the Coordinated Energy and Water Cycle Observation Project (CEOP) Enhanced Observing Period 3 (EOP-3) Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment (GEWEX) Americas Prediction Project (GAPP) Ft. Peck 30 Minute Flux Data Set. This data set contains 30 minute data from the single Ft. Peck station from the Ft. Peck reference site for the CEOP EOP-3 time period. This dataset only contains the first half of the EOP-3 time period (i.e. 1 October 2002 through 31 March 2003).

This data set contains both ASCII data and netCDF data. The ASCII data file covers the entire time period for all stations. The netCDF data file covers the entire time period with one netCDF file for each station.

title: Boundary Layer Height Estimates
summary: This dataset is an EXCEL document from the PASE project, collected from the NCAR/NSF C-130 Aircraft.

title: COMET CASE 016 Radiosonde Data
summary: This dataset contains radiosonde observation data in GEMPAK formatted files.  There is one file per day containing data for 00Z and 12Z.

title: GCIP/EAOP-98 Radar: LMRFC WSR-88D Stage III Hourly Precipitation Imagery (GIF)
summary: This data set contains data from the NOAA Lower Mississippi River Forecast Center (LMRFC). The LMRFC routinely ingests WSR-88D precipitation derived products (Level III) from  each of the radar sites with coverage in the Lower  Mississippi River Basin. In addition the LMRFC ingests  real-time precipitation data from several hundred gages.  The LMRFC produces a number of derived or Stage" products  using the radar and precipitation gage data. A Stage II  product is produced by merging radar precipitation  estimates  (Stage I) with ground truth data  provided by  the gages. The Stage II estimates are then composited into  a Stage III precipitation 4 x 4 km resolution area averaged mosaic for the Lower Mississippi River Basin. "

title: MATERHORN-X Tower Data
summary: This dataset contains flux tower and extensive energy balance data collected at all tower sites for the Mountain Terrain Atmospheric Modeling and Observations (MATERHORN-X) project. The data are raw and in comma delimited ASCII files. This dataset is very large and should be ordered in segments. If you wish to obtain this complete dataset, please send your request to eol-archive@ucar.edu.

title: Low Rate (LRT - 1 sps) Navigation data subset (ICARTT format) [NCAR/EOL]
summary:
This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the NSF/NCAR Research Aviation Facility (RAF) Gulfstream V HIAPER (NSF/NCAR GV HIAPER) aircraft (Tail Number N677F) during the Deep Convective Clouds and Chemistry Project (DC3) project from 18 May 2012 to 30 June 2012. This data set is a subset of the low rate aircraft data that contains a select set of the navigation parameters.

This data set is in ICARTT format. Please see the header portion of the data files for details on instruments, parameters, quality assurance, quality control, contact information, and data set comments.

title: COMET CASE 004 WSR-88D Base Reflectivity (third-lowest tilt angle) from Springfield, MO (SGF)
summary: This dataset contains the base reflectivity (third-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the Springfield, MO (SGF) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: NEXRAD CYS (Cheyenne,WY) Reflectivity and Velocity Imagery
summary: This dataset includes NEXRAD Reflectivity and Velocity Imagery from the VORTEX2 2009 and 2010 Field Catalogs. These imagery products are taken from the NEXRAD station located in Cheyenne, WY. The files are in .gif format.  Imagery files are only available for the VORTEX2 field phases for approximately May-June 2009 and April-June 2010. See the related links below to access the field catalogs for the exact time periods covered by this data set.

title: NOAA POES AVHRR
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: NOAA/ESRL/PSD NAME Supersite (Obispo) Meteorological Data
summary: This dataset contains the surface meteorological data collected from the Estacion Obispo Supersite for NAME.

title: Alaskan Lake Database Mapped from Landsat Images
summary:
The lake map for the State of Alaska was generated from selected Landsat acquired during summer seasons of circa 2000. Nearly 400 30-m resolution Enhanced Thematic Mapper Plus (ETM+) images were used to produce the lake map. The database contains over 38,000 lakes larger than 0.1 km2. The spatial coverage of the product is nearly the entire state except the Aleutian islands. The lake product is released at three different levels in response to lake size classes:

  • Level 1: large lakes greater than 10 km2;
  • Level 2: medium-sized lakes between 1 and 10 km2;
  • Level 3: small lakes between 0.1 and 1 km2.

The Alaskan lake products are released in ArcView shapefile format.

title: PRELIMINARY Sample Rate (SRT) Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics Flight-Level Data
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the NSF/NCAR HIAPER GV aircraft (Tail Number N677F) during the ARISTO2017 project. This dataset contains sample rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in netCDF format. These are PRELIMINARY FIELD-PHASE data and are not for publication. Final, production data (with calibrated values in engineering units) having the highest-quality that RAF can provide will be available within 6 months of the end of the project.

title: NSF/NCAR GV HIAPER Instrument Status Reports
summary: This dataset provides a link to the DC3 Field Catalog Reports section which includes NSF/NCAR GV HIAPER Instrument Status Reports

title: Geochemical analyses of Icelandic tephra preserved in lake sediments
summary: This data set contains major element geochemical analyses of tephra grains isolated from lake sediment recovered in continuous cores from lakes in Iceland, Svalbard, Arctic Canada, and from marine sediment cores from Greenland and Iceland.

title: Biomass Data [Grebmeier-Cooper] - Preliminary
summary:
Biomass is in gC/m2

Note: This dataset is preliminary.

title: ABLE 915 MHz Profiler RASS Data
summary: This data set contains temperature profile data from the Argonne National Laboratory ABLE (Atmospheric Boundary Layer Experiments), during the Cooperative Atmospheric Surface Exchange Study 1999 (CASES-99). Data were collected from 1 October 1999 to 2 October 1999, and are in ASCII text format. 915 MHz profilers were located at Whitewater, Beaumont, and Oxford, Kansas.

title: Lake-ICE upper air: High Resolution Research Soundings from Bellterre
summary: This data set contains ten second vertical resolution sounding data for Bellterre, Quebec Canada. This site was operated by The Atmospheric Technology Division (ATD) of the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research (UCAR). This data have undergone ATD and The Joint Office of Science Support (JOSS) quality control procedures. See the README for more information. Note, the README contains a complete list of available rawinsonde release times.

title: JMA Typhoon Ensemble Forecasts All Members Regional Scale Imagery
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: COMET CASE 044 base reflectivity, 124 nmi range, 2.40/2.50 degree from BMX
summary: This dataset contains the  base reflectivity, 124 nmi range, 2.40/2.50 degrees elevation angle data product archived from the  BIRMINGHAM, AL BMX radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: CSET Field Catalog Upper Air Products
summary: This dataset provides a link to the CSET Field Catalog Upper Air Products section which includes dropsondes and regional radiosonde skewts.

title: ARM Organic Carbon and Organic Matter Soils Data Set
summary: The Department of Energy (DOE) Atmospheric Radiation Measurement (ARM) Southern Great Plains (SGP) Organic Carbon and Organic Matter Soils Data Set is one of the various sub-surface data sets developed for the ARM/GCIP (Global Energy and Water Cycle Experiment ?GEWEX? Continental-scale International Project) 1996 Near-Surface Observation (NESOB-96) Data Set. This data set contains a summary table of the measured organic carbon percentage and the estimated organic matter percentage in the near surface soil at each of the ARM SWATS (Soil Water and Temperature System) sites at the SGP site. The soil characterizations were perfomed by Oklahoma State University. No additional quality control was performed by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: HLY-02-01 Bio-Optics Station Information [Hill, V.]
summary: This data set contains information collected during the SBI Spring 2002 Cruise aboard the U.S. Coast Guard Cutter (USCGC) Healy (HLY-02-01). This data set consists of detailed station sheet information and photos. The station photos were normally taken before the Conductivity Temperature Depth (CTD) - productivity cast and after the SPMR/SMSR cast. Data for the Summer 2002 cruise of the same type can be found as a companion data set.

title: Ship Radar
summary:
This dataset includes microfilm of various radar footage (including, but not limited to Hybrid and Compacted) from ships for Phases I, II, and III of the Global Atmospheric Research Program's (GARP) Atlantic Tropical Experiment (GATE) Title, vessel(s), and phase(s) are specified in the Description" section on the order page.

"
archive_note: These data are available on microfilm however we do not have the capability to digitize or replicate and ship them.  They are available for viewing on location at the NCAR Foothills Laboratory using our microfilm viewer.

title: NOAA Aeronomy Laboratory Tropical Dynamics and Climate Group Wind Profiler Data
summary: NULL

title: CAMP: Himalayas Hourly Surface Meteorology, Flux, and Radiation Data Set
summary: This data set contains the Coordinated Energy and Water Cycle Observation (CEOP) Enhanced Observing Period 1 (EOP-1) CEOP related Asian Monsoon Experiment (CAMP) Himalayas Hourly Surface Meteorology, Flux, and Radiation Data Set.  This data set contains hourly data from a single station (Pyramid) for the CEOP EOP-1 time period (01 July 2001 to 30 September 2001).  The National Center for Atmospheric Research/Earth Observing Laboratory (NCAR/EOL) did not perform quality control processing on this data set.

title: BALTEX: Lindenberg Soil Temperature Raw Data (10 min)
summary: This is the 10 minute soil temperature data for the Baltex Lindenberg Site.

title: NOAA/ATDD Belle Mina, Alabama Doppler Lidar Vertical Wind, Backscatter and Cloud Base Height Data
summary: This data set contains vertical wind and backscatter profiles as well as cloud base height data from the Leosphere WINDCUBE 100s Doppler Lidar that NOAA/ATDD deployed at Belle Mina, Alabama during the VORTEX-SE 2016 field campaign. This doppler lidar was deployed on 11 March 2016 after the CLAMPS doppler lidar stopped operations on 9 March. See the companion data set below for the CLAMPS doppler lidar observations from 2-9 March 2016. These data are in NetCDF format.

title: Mobile TTUKa Radar Data (2010, only)
summary: This dataset contains data collected by the Texas Tech Ka-band (TTUKa) during the VORTEX2 project. These data are organized into separate zip files corresponding to the date of the event. Data from 2010 only is available here. Please directly contact the data provider, listed at the bottom of the page, for data from the 2009 field campaign.

title: UAH MoDLS Doppler Lidar Data
summary: This data set contains wind profile, vertical stare, and Velocity-Azimuth Display (VAD) data from the University of Alabama-Huntsville (UAH) Doppler Lidar during the 2017 VORTEX-SE field season. The Doppler Lidar is part of the UAH Mobile Doppler Lidar and Soundings (MoDLS) system. The data set includes the raw data and processed data.

title: UMRBPP Hydrology: Co-operative Agency Reservoir Data
summary: This dataset contains Co-operative Agency Reservoir Month-end reservoir data from sites reported within the UMRBPP domain. No additional quality control was performed by UCAR/JOSS.

title: COMET CASE 044 storm total precip accumulation from CLE
summary: This dataset contains the  storm total precip accumulation data product archived from the  CLEVELAND, OH/Cleveland CLE radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: PRELIMINARY Sample Rate (SRT) Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics Flight-Level Data
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the NSF/NCAR HIAPER GV aircraft (Tail Number N677F) during the OTREC-TEST project. This dataset contains sample rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in netCDF format. These are PRELIMINARY FIELD-PHASE data and are not for publication. Final, production data (with calibrated values in engineering units) having the highest-quality that RAF can provide will be available within 6 months of the end of the project.

title: COMET CASE 018 WSR-88D Radial Velocity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) from BUFFALO, NY
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Radial Velocity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  BUFFALO, NY/Cheektowaga (BUF) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: WRF 4KM Relative Humidity Forecast Imagery (Craig to Torrington) [Dudhia (NCAR-MMM)]
summary: This dataset contains Weather Research and Forecasting Model (WRF) 4 kilometer vertical cross-sections of relative humidity. The imagery was generated from Craig, CO to Torrington, WY during the ICE-L project. It is available in PNG format and covers the time span from 2007-11-19 00:00:00 to 2007-12-21 23:59:59.

title: NCAR and Idaho Power Company SNOWIE Precipitation Gauges
summary: This dataset contains the NCAR (National Center for Atmospheric Research) and Idaho Power Company's (IPC) precipitation gauge data from 12 different sites during the SNOWIE (Seeded and Natural Orographic Wintertime Clouds: The Idaho Experiment) project. Data were collected from 7 January 2017 to 16 March 2017. The data frequency of IPC Geonor gauges is approximately 1/15 minute, and the frequency of NCAR gauges at Clear Creek and Silver Creek is 1 minute. These data are in readable ASCII text format. Data have been quality controlled. Please refer to the readme for more information.

title: Rawinsonde West Texas Mesonet SkewT Imagery (Lubbock) [Texas Tech]
summary: This dataset contains Rawinsonde West Texas Mesonet SkewT Imagery from Texas Tech.

title: LBA: Pantanal Surface Meteorology and Radiation Data Set
summary:
This data set contains the Coordinated Energy and Water Cycle Observation Project (CEOP) Enhanced Observing Period 3 (EOP-3) Large Scale Biosphere-Atmosphere Experiment in Amazonia (LBA) Pantanal Surface Meteorology and Radiation Data Set. This data set contains half-hourly data from a single station for the first half of the CEOP EOP-3 time period (01 October 2002 to 31 March 2003).

This data set contains both ASCII data and netCDF data. The ASCII data file covers the entire time period for all stations. The netCDF data file covers the entire time period with one netCDF file for each station.

title: ARM Mobile Facility Vaisala Laser Ceilometer Data
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: HLY-08-03 Raw Knudsen 320B/R Depth Sounder Data [Sambrotto/LDEO]
summary:
This dataset includes data from the Knudsen 320B/R Depth Sounder system onboard the US Coast Guard Cutter Healy during the Bering Sea Ecosystem Study-Bering Sea Integrated Ecosystem Research Program (BEST-BSIERP) 2008 0803 (summer) cruise. BEST-BSIERP together are the Bering Sea project. The Knudsen depth sounder records the 3 - 6 kHz data (Sub Bottom Profile) underway. There is one tar file for each day. The following is a list of the file extensions and their meaning of the files contained in the tar files:

.keb - Binary Knudsen Playback File
.kea - ASCII log of depth, settings and environmental data
.sgy - Binary SEG-Y extended Seismic format.

title: Carbon and Nitrogen Isotope Dynamics (ASCII) [Dunton, K.]
summary: Biological material from three levels in the ocean (POM, plankton, benthos) was collected to determine the natural abundance of d13C (carbon) and d15N (nitrogen). Isotope data were used to trace the advection of northward flowing organic material through the Bering Strait into the Chukchi and Bering Seas. Isotope signatures also provided information about the trophic links between pelagic and benthic components of the shelf and slope within the study area. These data are in ASCII format.

title: COMET CASE 017 WSR-88D Base Reflectivity (second-lowest tilt angle) from Phoenix, AZ (IWA)
summary: This dataset contains the base reflectivity (second-lowest  tilt angle) data product archived from the Phoenix, AZ (IWA)radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: FAAM BAe-146 CAPS Data
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: Satellite NOAA polar orbiter IR Composite Image.(GIF) [Univ. Of Alaska, Geophysical Institute]
summary: This data set contains infrared IR composite image from the NOAA polar orbiter AVHRR data. Images were produced every 2 hours from the University of Alaska Geophysical Institute.

title: CaPE Sky Photography and Video
summary: Routine sky photography was taken at 5 primary sites KSC,   Melbourne Beach, CP-2, CP-3 and CP-4 radar sites.  These included 35 mm slides, 16 mm time lapse video (usually 10 or30 second frames) and movie or video cameras at coastal     sites.  Also a time lapse video was taken from a camera at  KSC.

title: COMET CASE 021 NWS Textual Weather Products
summary: This dataset contains the text products issued by the National Weather Service. These include forecasts, watches, warnings, local and national discussions, as well as coded surface observations and upper air soundings.  The files  are named based on the type of product and the issuance time.

title: ACE-1: Cape Grim NOx Measurements (Galbally)
summary: This Dataset consists of continuous measurements of NO, NO2, and NOx concentrations taken at Cape Grim monitoring station. Whilst the data have been edited to remove bad data caused by known instrument malfunctions, a detailed item-by-item examination of the data has not been performed.

title: Ice Camp (PRELIMINARY) CTD Yoyo Cast Analysis Depth (ASCII) (PSC) [Morison, J.]
summary: This data set contains data from a PRELIMINARY analysis of every 10th downcast of the yoyo Conductivity Temperature Depth (CTD) between the start of SHEBA and the end of January 1998. It is made from Tim Stanton's field summary data analysis. These are the data that were shown in contour form at the March 1998 meeting. This particular data set contains data on depth, giving the 101 sample depths. See also the companion data sets containing time (13.727), Temperature (13.728), Salinity (13.729), and Density (13.730).

title: P-3 Meteorological State and Navigation Parameters - slow data (netCDF) [NOAA/AOC]
summary:
This dataset contains the NOAA P-3 (N43RF) State and Navigation parameters from the missions flown during SALLJEX. These netCDF files contain the raw (type 4 record) slow data from the NOAA/AOC standard tape in netCDF format.

SALLJEX was funded by NOAA/OGP, NSF(ATM0106776) and funding agencies from Brazil FAPESP Grant 01/13816-1) and Argentina (ANPCYT PICT 07-06671, UBACyT 055)

title: NASA DC-8 PTRMS Methanol Data
summary: This data set contains NASA DC-8 Proton Transfer Reaction Mass Spectrometer (PTRMS) Methanol Data collected during the Deep Convective Clouds and Chemistry Experiment (DC3) from 18 May 2012 through 22 June 2012. This data set is in ICARTT format. Please see the header portion of the data files for details on instruments, parameters, quality assurance, quality control, contact information, and data set comments

title: Radar Echo Top Graphics Data
summary:
This dataset includes microfilm of radar echo graphics data for Oceanographer and Researcher for Phases I, II, and III of the Global Atmospheric Research Program's (GARP) Atlantic Tropical Experiment (GATE). Phase is noted in the Description" section on the order page.

"
archive_note: These data are available on microfilm however we do not have the capability to digitize or replicate and ship them.  They are available for viewing on location at the NCAR Foothills Laboratory using our microfilm viewer.

title: GOES-11 Leg45 NCRG-NZCH-AGGH 5km Ch3 Water Vapor Satellite Imagery
summary: This dataset contains leg45 NCRG-NZCH-AGGH 5km Channel 3 water vapor imagery from the GOES-11 satellite taken during the HIPPO-3 project. The imagery are in JPG format. The imagery cover the time span from 2010-03-09 10:57:00 to 2010-04-20 14:52:00.

title: HLY-02-01 Satellite DMSP and HRPT Overpass Data [NCAR/EOL]
summary: This data set contains the satellite DMSP and HRPT overpass data. During the 2002 Spring and Summer Cruises of SBI all HRPT and DMSP overpasses of the U.S. Coast Guard Cutter (USCGC) Healy were archived to tape. These files were collected with a Terascan receiving system aboard the Healy as it cruised the Bering and Chukchi Seas. These data are archived as pass files on 4mm DDS-3 tapes using the Terascan archive function. Please see the accompanying documentation files for the spring cruise and summer cruise for a complete catalog of overpasses on each tape.
archive_note: Please email the Point of Contact to request these data.

title: Ivotuk Otuk Creek Discharge (ASCII) [Sturm, M.]
summary: This dataset contains Otuk Creek discharge data taken by the Snow, Shrubs, and Weather Group at the Ivotuk site as part of the ATLAS project. Measurements were taken every hour during the melt of 2000. See the readme file for the investigator's notes.

title: CIRES Tethered Lifting System Processed Data (ASCII) [Balsley]
summary: This dataset contains data from the CIRES Tethered Lifting System (TLS). This is the processed data in ascii. The proccessed data contains atmospheric and turbulence parameters sampled at 1 Hz.

title: COMET CASE 020 WSR-88D Base Reflectivity (second-lowest tilt angle) from CENTRAL PENNSYLVANIA
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Base Reflectivity (second-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  CENTRAL PENNSYLVANIA (CCX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: Aircraft NCAR C-130 High-rate Data (netCDF) [NCAR/RAF]
summary: High-rate data in netCDF format is available here for each flight of the NCAR C-130 that occurred during the SHEBA project (16 flights total) in the spring and summer of 1998. The following is a list of research flight numbers and corresponding dates/times: (rf01a 1846 5/4/98 - 0017 5/5) (rf01b 0036 5/5 - 0350 5/5) (rf02 1849 5/7 - 0220 5/8) (rf03 1808 5/11 - 0312 5/12) (rf04 1824 5/15 - 0256 5/16) (rf05 1652 5/18 - 0330 5/19) (rf06 1655 5/20 - 0300 5/21) (rf07 1653 5/24 - 0327 5/25) (rf08 1652 5/27 - 0312 5/28) (rf09 1630 7/8 - 0318 7/9) (rf10 1658 7/15 - 0250 7/16) (rf11 1635 7/18 - 0335 7/19) (rf12 1608 7/21 - 0254 7/22) (rf13 1627 7/23 - 0332 7/24) (rf14 1547 7/26 - 0004 7/27) (rf15 1556 7/28 - 0003 7/29) (rf16 1658 7/29 - 0004 7/30). The SHEBA C-130 dataset documentation (most of the materials made available in the previously-released data notebooks) have been put on-line via the NCAR RAF Web site. This will enable all users of the data to access the most critical documentation and data quality materials and to assemble their own copies of the documentation package. This documentation web site may be reached by selecting the data set named SHEBA: Aircraft NCAR C-130 Documentation and Data Quality Materials.

title: High Rate (HRT - 25 sps) Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics Flight-Level Data
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the NSF/NCAR L188 Electra aircraft (Tail Number N595KR) operated by NCAR from 1973-1977. This dataset contains high rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in netCDF format collected during the AIDJEX-II project.

title: GCIP/EOP Radar: Composite Radar Imagery (GIF)
summary: This dataset contains images generated from the the WSI  NIDS 2 km national radar mosaic for the GCIP/EOP period. One image per day is loaded with a 48 hour delay.  These data are provided for data browsing purposes.

title: Ivotuk Flux Data - Shrub Site (ASCII) [Beringer, J.]
summary:
This dataset includes flux data from the Shrub site near Ivotuk gathered during the 1998 summer field season. Surface energy and trace gas exchange measurements were made at each of the Ivotuk sites using the eddy covariance technique. The MAT site was operated continuously over the growing season whilst the remaining sites were characterized by a single tower that was moved from site to site. The MAT site is therefore used as a reference.

This dataset is available in both ASCII and EXCEL formats - For data browsing, we suggest ordering the EXCEL version and using EXCEL to plot the data. NOTE: This dataset contains the data in ASCII format.

title: Council Site Characteristics [Beringer, J.]
summary: This dataset includes diagrams and photos of the sites in the Council region gathered during the 2000 summer field season. It is in MS Word format.

title: Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics HRT Data in GENPROI format
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the QueenAir, A-80 aircraft (Tail Number N304D) during the MIC-78 project. This dataset contains high rate (primarily 10sps) navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in GENPRO-I format.

title: GMAO GEOS-5 Forecast Products Imagery - Animation CO 800-500hpa KBJC PANC
summary: This dataset contains animated CO 800-500hpa KBJC PANC GMAO GEOS-5 forecast imagery taken during the HIPPO project. The data is in GIF format. The data covers the time span from 2008-01-05 12:00:00 to 2009-01-05 12:00:00.

title: Council Understory Flux Data - Spruce Forest Site (Excel) [Beringer, J.]
summary: This dataset includes flux data from the spruce forest site area in the Council region gathered during the 2000 summer field season in Excel format.

title: Tenago Del Aire Criteria Pollutants and Meteorological Data (CDP) \t
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: COMET CASE 004 WSR-88D Base Reflectivity (lowest tilt angle) from Saint Louis, MO (LSX)
summary: This dataset contains the base reflectivity (lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the Saint Louis, MO (LSX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: GCIP/LSA-NW 00 Surface: LDM WMO Hourly Surface Data in QC format
summary: The Unidata Local Data Manager (LDM) World Meteorological Organization (WMO) Hourly Surface data in QC format is one of several surface datasets provided in the GEWEX Continental-Scale International Project (GCIP) Large Scale Area-North West (LSA-NW) Enhanced Annual Observing Period (EAOP) 2000. This dataset contains data for the GCIP LSA-NW EAOP-00 domain and time period (01 April 2000 through 31 March 2001).  The GCIP LSA-NW EAOP-00 domain is approximately 90W to 115W longitude and 36N to 51N latitude. These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: NSSL Weather Research and Forecasting (WRF)
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: MM5 FLEXPART Forecast Product Imagery [NCAR/EOL]
summary: This dataset contains MM5 FLEXPART forecast product model imagery collected during the MILAGRO field project.

title: Measurements of little auks (Alle alle) at Kap Hoegh, Greenland in 2007
summary: This dataset contains measurements at the Kap Hoegh, Greenland little auk colony in 2007. These data are chick growth measurements, productivity and attendance, morphometric measurements of adults used in different studies including time depth recorder (TDR), doubly labeled water measurements, stable isotope, geolocators, and survival measurements. Data are contained in a single Excel file.

title: S-Pol Radar, miscellaneous special data sets including scan images and vertical pointing
summary: This dataset contains 6 tar files with scan images in gif format, a tar file with sun scans and a tar file with vertically pointing scans.

title: COMET CASE 042 Ship and Buoy Observations
summary: This dataset contains ship and buoy observation data in GEMPAK formatted files. There is one file per day containing data for every sixth hour  of the day.

title: NOAA Profiler Network (NPN) Data [NCAR/EOL]
summary: These data are in netCDF format. These data are hourly, and include wind and surface data.

title: Sediment Oxygen Flux Data in the Bering Sea Shelf
summary: The high productivity in the Bering sea coupled with shallow water depths over the shelf result in a large fraction of the productivity reaching the sediments. This fuels the productive benthic ecosystem there. It also results in high benthic oxygen consumption and denitrification rates. The goal of our project is to look at the benthic geochemistry in the Bering Sea Ecosystem Study-Bering Sea Integrated Ecosystem Research Program (BEST-BSIERP) region, especially the benthic cycling of nitrogen. BEST-BSIERP together are the Bering Sea project.

title: BALTEX: Lindenberg RASS Raw Data (30 min)
summary: This is the 30 minute RASS data for the Baltex Lindenberg Site. This data contains time, vertical resolution, height, average time interval, and virtual temperature.

title: NCAR ISS GAUS (MAPR Site) Rawinsonde Data (ESC format) [NCAR/EOL]
summary: The Terrain Induced Rotor Experiment (T-REX) was conducted during March and April 2006, during which time 102 radiosondes were launched using a fix sounding system located near Independence, California. T-REX is the second phase of a coordinated effort to explore the structure and evolution of atmospheric rotors, which typically occur parallel to, and downstream from, mountain ridge crests. The first phase was a project conducted in 2004 called the Sierra Rotors Project. Both phases included upwind radiosonde launches, from the California Central Valley, used to help predict the onset of events likely to produce rotors on the lee side of the Sierra Nevada Mountain Range. Soundings were also launched in the Owens Valley from an Integrated Sounding System (ISS).

title: 1s Merged dataset of all C-130 observations and GEOS-Chem near-realtime simulations for WINTER
summary:
This dataset contains all Wintertime Investigation of Transport, Emission, and Reactivity (WINTER) C-130 observations merged at the 1 second time steps. In addition to the observations, the dataset also contains results from the GEOS-Chem near-realtime simulation sampled along the flight track. Refer to the instrument's dataset for instrument description. The GEOS-Chem model description can be found at www.geos-chem.org. Missing values are indicated by -99999. When generating fine time resolution data from a coarser resolution, the reported value at the original (coarse) time step is applied uniformly to all intermediate (fine) time steps - no interpolation is performed. When generating coarse time resolution data from a finer resolution, the time weighted average of the values at the intermediate (fine) time steps is used as the value at the coarser time step. Please follow the WINTER data policy.

These data were updated April 7, 2016. The revised set uses the final data uploaded to the WINTER archive as of 4th April 2016.

title: Russian Historical Soil Temperature Data

Data were recovered from many sources and compiled by staff at the University of Colorado, USA, and the Russian Academy of Sciences in Puschino, Russia. Soil temperatures were measured at depths of 0.02 to 3.2 m using bent stem thermometers, extraction thermometers, and electrical resistance thermistors. Data coverage extends from the 1800s through 1990, but is not continuous. Data are not available for all stations for the entire period of coverage. For example, data collection began at many stations in the 1930s and 1950s, and not all stations continued taking measurements through 1990. This research was supported by the National Science Foundation (NSF) Office of Polar Programs (OPP) awards OPP-9614557, OPP-9907541, and OPP-0229766. Data are available as tar.gz files.

title: History of the Arctic Flora in North America
summary:
This dataset in an attempt to increase understanding of how climate cycles of the Quaternary (the last 2.6 million years) impacted divergence in Arctic and alpine tundra flora. Specimens were collected in Beringia and the mountains of western North America, focusing on populations existing within (western and eastern Beringia, and the Pacific Northwest and Rocky Mountains, respectively), as well as sites between those refugia. Briefly, DNA was sequenced from chloroplast and nuclear loci for multiple species of tundra plants that inhabited the entire study region. Target species (Campanula species, Kobresia myosuroides, Lloydia serotina, Pinguicula vulgaris, Poa alpina, Rhodiola species, and Saxifraga species) were phylogenetically diverse and displayed a range of dispersal abilities, making them excellent candidates for evaluating general history of the tundra. Those genetic data make up this Arctic Flora dataset. From the genetic sequence data, gene trees are being reconstructed and used to estimate the patterns and timing of divergence, test which geologic and climatic events most impacted divergence, and infer how the process of genetic divergence differed between Arctic and alpine tundra refugia.

The data is archived in nexus files - the standard format for aligned sequence data ready to be used in a phylogenetic analysis. The files are separated by taxon and genetic locus within a given taxon. The nexus format provides details on the data type (DNA), number of samples, and length of sequence. Within a file, all the sequences are aligned but not interleaved, such that the 'sample name' is followed by the entire sequence for that sample. All the specimens that were collected are archived and publicly accessible in the Western Washington University Herbarium.
