title: NRL COAMPS TC 5km Forecast [NRL]
summary: This data set contains NRL COAMPS 5km TC model forecast imagery over the Western Pacific Ocean. Products include surface winds, 850mb vorticity and winds, radar reflectivity, sea level pressure, surface enthalpy, total precipitable water, and forecast track and maximum winds. Products are available during periods of active tropical cyclones and are available every six hours to 120 hours. The region covered by each run is specific to the tropical storm. These images were developed by NRL and are in gif format.

title: Low Rate (LRT - 1 sps) Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics Flight-Level Data
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the NSF/NCAR L188 Electra aircraft (Tail Number N595KR) operated by NCAR from 1973-1977. This dataset contains low rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in netCDF format collected during the GAMETAG-76 project.

title: FASTEX soundings from ASAP ship Fort Desaix
summary: This dataset consists of sounding data from the French ASAP ship the Fort Desaix.  Soundings were taken two times per day (00 and 12 UTC) while the ship was within the FASTEX domain.  These data were processed through the automated and visual quality control.  This dataset includes  pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude taken at 10 second vertical intervals.  Refer to the station README for  details.

title: COMET CASE 020 WSR-88D Radial Velocity (lowest tilt angle) from WAKEFIELD, VA/Ellendale
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Radial Velocity (lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  WAKEFIELD, VA/Ellendale (DOX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: GOES South Pacific Winds IR Satellite Imagery
summary: This dataset contains South Pacific winds IR imagery from the GOES satellite taken during the HIPPO-3 project. The imagery are in GIF format. The imagery cover the time span from 2010-03-17 00:00:00 to 2010-04-19 21:00:00.

title: COMET CASE 020 Layer Reflectivity (third-lowest tilt angle) from BURLINGTON, VT
summary: This dataset contains the  Layer Reflectivity (third-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  BURLINGTON, VT (CXX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: COMET CASE 018 WSR-88D One-Hour Precipitation Estimate from SIOUX FALLS, SD
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D One-Hour Precipitation Estimate data product archived from the  SIOUX FALLS, SD/Sioux Falls (FSD) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: ECMWF 125km Assimilated Products Imagery - GEMS O3 Global Surface [(MACC)]
summary: This dataset contains global ECMWF 125km Assimilated Products Imagery of surface GEMS ozone taken during the HIPPO-2 project. The imagery are in GIF format. The imagery cover the time span from 2009-10-26 00:00:00 to 2009-11-25 00:00:00.

title: GOES 12 4KM Channel 4 Thermal IR Imagery
summary: This dataset includes GOES 12 4km Channel 4 Thermal IR Imagery from the VORTEX2 field catalog. The files are jpg images. See the catalog link in the related links section below to access the field catalog.

title: Brazil Sao Borja Micro Rain Radar Data
summary: This data set contains the raw spectra, average, and processed data from the Micro Rain Radar that was located in Sao Borja, Brazil during the RELAMPAGO (Remote sensing of Electrification, Lightning, And Meso-scale/micro-scale Processes with Adaptive Ground Observations) field season. The radar was operated by INPE (Instituto Nacional de Pesquisas Espaciais)

title: NOAA N42 P-3 Photography Cloud Videos [NOAA/AOC]
summary: This dataset contains cloud videos collected by the N42 during its flights into hurricanes between July 3rd, 2005 to July 24th, 2005 by cameras that pointed forward, downward and out the right and left side of the aircraft.

title: COMET CASE 032 WSR-88D Radial Velocity (third-lowest tilt angle) from CENTRAL PENNSYLVANIA
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Radial Velocity (third-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  CENTRAL PENNSYLVANIA (CCX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: CIRPAS Twin Otter 1-hz PCASP Drop Size Spectra - NASA Ames format
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the CIRPAS Twin Otter aircraft during the Physics of Stratocumulus Tops" (POST) project off the west coast of Monterey
archive_note: CA. This data set contains 1 hertz (1 sps) PCASP Drop Size Spectra. The files are the final data in NASA Ames format."

title: ACE-ASIA Satellite: Seastar SeaWIFS [Imagery]
summary: The ACE-ASIA Satellite: Seastar SeaWIFS ?Imagery? are available online. All data is in JPG format.

title: Darwin French Falcon ROBUST Probe Total Water Content (TWC) Data
summary: This dataset contains Total Water Content (TWC) data from the High Altitude Ice Crystals - High Ice Water Content (HAIC-HIWC) project that took place in Darwin, Australia. The data is from the ROBUST probe on the French Falcon, operated by SAFIRE. The files are csv files and contain the UTC time and the TWC.

title: WSR-88D Level 2 and 3 Data (nids Format)
summary: This dataset contains a link to the NOAA/NCDC WSR88D radar archives of Level II and Level III data.

title: COMET CASE 005 WSI NIDS Three-hour Precipitation Estimate from Rush, PA
summary: This dataset contains the Three-hour Precipitation Estimate data product archived from the WSI NIDS datastream for the Rush, PA radar. Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format, at a frequency of 10 minutes.

title: Water Temperature and Bathymetric Depth Soundings for Lakes near Barrow
summary:
This dataset contains Water Temperature and Bathymetric Depth Soundings for Lakes near Barrow, AK. Onset Water Temperature Pro v2 loggers were used in each of the five lakes. Loggers were attached to a cable which had an anchor (sandbag) and float. One logger was always near the float and one near the sandbag to obtain the upper and lower measurements in the water column. Replicate measurements were obtained, with one thermistor string on the north side of the lake, and one on the south side.

Deployed on a Zodiac inflatable boat and outboard motor, a Lowrance/Eagle SeaCharter 502c DF iGPS Sonar Unit obtained high frequency water depth soundings in August 2008. These sonar tracks are plotted on satellite imagery for all five lakes.

title: Satellite NOAA-14 VIS images (GIF) [Univ. of Wisconsin, SSEC]
summary: This data set contains NOAA-14 VIS images (GIF) provided by SSEC at the University of Wisconsin. Images are available at 2200 UTC beginning on 3/9/98. Image resolution is 5 km.

title: NOAA/ESRL/PSD NAME Supersite (Obispo) RASS Imagery [NCAR/EOL]
summary: This dataset contains RASS imagery from the NOAA/ESRL/PSD supersite at Obispo.

title: ISS Surface Meteorology Data [NCAR/EOL]
summary: This dataset contains surface meteorology data collected by the NCAR/EOL Integrated Sounding System (ISS) that was located at the Homestead Profiling Site" near Elmwood
archive_note:
OK during the International H2O Project (IHOP_2002). These data are available in daily netCDF files and have not been quality controlled.

"

title: COMET CASE 008 WSR-88D Storm Total Precipitation Estimate from Sacramento, CA (DAX)
summary: This dataset contains the Storm Total Precipitation Estimate data product archived from the Sacramento, CA (DAX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: Hydrometeorological Automated Data System (HADS)
summary: This dataset contains a link to the Hydrometeorological Automated Data System (HADS) website.

title: HX-250 ADCP Data [Woodgate, R.]
summary: This is edited ship's Acoustic Doppler Current Profiler (ADCP) and SS (sea surface) underway data from the Alpha Helix mooring recovery and redeployment cruise September 2001. Data processed by Seth Danielson, University of Alaska Fairbanks (UAF). ADCP data quality control (QC) is described in the documentation. SS data have been only minimally cleaned up. Unedited underway data are available elsewhere in this archive.

title: COMET CASE 007 GOES-8 VIS at 2km (Unidata-Wisconsin floating region)
summary: This dataset contains GOES-8 VIS imagery at 2km resolution. The data is from a floating region distributed on the Unidata-Wisconsin data stream.  Data is archived as McIDAS AREA files.

title: CACTI Particle Soot Absorption Photometer (PSAP) Data
summary: This dataset contains a link to the DOE ARM Archive CACTI Particle Soot Absorption Photometer (PSAP) data. You must have an ARM Archive account to access these data.

title: DOE Gulf Stream 1 (G-1) Navigation and State Parameters
summary: This dataset contains a link to the DOE ARM Archive Gulf Stream 1 (G-1) Navigation and State Parameters for the VOCALS campaign. You must have an ARM Archive account to access the data.

title: Beaufort Gyre IOEB Data 1992-1998 (Unix format) [Krishfield, R.]
summary: This dataset consists of sensor data collected aboard buoys in the Beaufort sea. The sensor data are prefiltered, combined, adjusted for buoy drift and screened with a Gaussian first difference filter. This dataset exists as 11 tarred UNIX files.

title: COMET CASE 044 relative mean radial V from OHX
summary: This dataset contains the  storm relative mean radial velocity, 2.40 degrees elevation angle (P) data product archived from the  NASHVILLE, TN/Old Hickory OHX radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: Harmful Algal Blooms Observing System (HABSOS)
summary: This dataset provides a link to the Harmful Algal Blooms Observing System (HABSOS) website. HABSOS is a data collection and distribution system for harmful algal bloom (HAB) information in the Gulf of Mexico.

title: COMET CASE 036 WSR-88D Radial Velocity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) from PORTLAND, OR
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Radial Velocity (fourth-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  PORTLAND, OR (RTX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: NSF C-130 Photography On-board Instrumentation Photographs
summary: This dataset provides a link to a photo gallery containing photos from the NSF/NCAR C-130 instrumentation for the INDOEX campaign.

title: COMET CASE 004 (BOW ECHO) WSI NIDS 0.5 degree Storm Relative Velocity from Paducah, KY
summary: This dataset contains the 0.5 degree Storm Relative Velocity data product archived from the WSI NIDS datastream for the Paducah, KY radar. Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format, at a frequency of 5 minutes.

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Upper Air:NOAA 405Mhz Profiler Dataset
summary: The NESOB-97 National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) 405 MHZ Wind Profiler Network Dataset consists of hourly  winds from sixteen NOAA Profiler Network (NPN) sites. The profiles  contain total wind speed, wind direction, U and V wind  components, and altitude.  No additional quality control was  performed. When attempting to preview a profile, use altitude  and either wind direction or speed since pressure is always  missing. Please see the README for more details.

title: NCAR GV Flight Plan Reports
summary: This dataset provides a link to the PREDICT Field Catalog Reports section which includes NCAR GV Flight Plan Reports.

title: CCOPE-2015 Parsivel Disdrometer Data
summary: This dataset contains data from a Parsivel disdrometer deployed during the 2015 Chilean Coastal Orographic Precipitation Experiment (CCOPE-2015). Information on the overall goals of CCOPE-2015, deployment strategy, and some results are found in Massmann, et al. (2017). All data were collected at Curanilahue, Chile (CRL).

title: Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics HRT Data in NetCDF format
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the NCAR Research Aviation Facility (RAF) King Air aircraft (Tail Number: N312D) during the Convective Waves (CONV_WAVES) project. This dataset contains high rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in NetCDF format.

title: NSSL MGAUS Radiosonde Data (ESC FORMAT) [NCAR/EOL]
summary: The Verification of the Origins of Rotation in Tornadoes Experiment (VORTEX) is a project aimed at investigating tornado genesis and examining tornado structure and evolution using a suite of atmostpheric instruments. The VORTEX2 field campaign included the use of four mobile GPS Advanced Upper_Air Sounding (GAUS) systems. This dataset contains 117 radiosonde soundings collected during the 2009 field campaign (May 11 - June 14, 2009) and 186 radiosonde soundings collected during the 2010 field campaign (May 6 - June 15, 2010) from two of the systems that were operated by the NOAA National Severe Storm Laboratory (NSSL).

title: WRF 4KM Surface Dewpoint Temperature Forecast Imagery [Dudhia (NCAR-MMM)]
summary: This dataset contains Weather Research and Forecast Model (WRF) 4 kilometer surface Dewpoint Temperature forecast imagery generated during the ICE-L project. The imagery is in PNG format and covers the time span from 2007-11-19 00:00:00 to 2007-12-21 23:59:59.

title: Aura OMI Satellite Data
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: COMET CASE 038 GOES_8 1km_efl2 at VIS
summary: This dataset contains GOES_8 1km_efl2 imagery at VIS resolution.  Data is archived as McIDAS AREA files.

title: COMET CASE 005 WSI NIDS from Binghamton, NY (GIF)
summary: This dataset contains WSI NIDS radar imagery from the BGM radar, Binghamton, NY. Data are archived as GIF files.

title: Model Output From the 'Frost Index' Permafrost Model: Variations in Circumpolar Frozen Ground Conditions and Modeled Future Conditions
summary: This data set contains permafrost distribution maps, active-layer thickness maps, and hazard-potential maps constructed using results from the 'frost index' permafrost model (Nelson and Outcalt, 1987) driven by modern climatic data and scenarios of climate change derived from three transient general circulation models (Greco et al., 1994). The permafrost maps show the distribution of permafrost in the Northern Hemisphere under modern climatic conditions and General Climate Model (GCM) projections for 2050; the active-layer thickness maps show relative changes in the depth of seasonal thawing projected for 2050; and the hazard-potential maps are used as indices to evaluate potential environmental hazards associated with thaw settlement and thermokarst.

title: WRF 4KM Mixing Ratio Forecast Imagery (Craig to Imperial) [Dudhia (NCAR-MMM)]
summary: This dataset contains Weather Research and Forecasting Model (WRF) 4 kilometer vertical cross-sections of four different mixing ratios, ice number concentration, and temperature. The imagery contains cloud water, rain water, snow, and Graupel mixing ratios. The imagery was generated from Craig, CO to Imperial, NE during the ICE-L project. It is available in PNG format and covers the time span from 2007-11-19 00:00:00 to 2007-12-21 23:59:59.

title: CSAE: Sabreliner Photography Cloud Videos
summary: This dataset consists of mpg files from video tape (VHS) from flights of the NCAR Sabreliner aircraft during the Contrail Studies Airborne Exhaust (CSAE) project. This dataset contains forward-looking video for some of the flights.

title: GCIP/NESOB-97 Surface: BLC/MPL Cloud Composite Dataset
summary: This dataset contains the GCIP/NESOB-97 ARMCART SGP Belfort Laser Ceiliometer (BLC) and MicroPulse Lidar (MPL) data for the NESOB-97 domain and time period. The 110-meter upward vertical offset present in the NESOB96 BLC data is not present in this dataset. These data were not quality controlled by the University Corporation for Atmospheric Research/Joint Office for Science Support (UCAR/JOSS).

title: Homestead GSFC Lidar Observatory for Winds (GLOW) 10 minute Data [NASA]
summary: This dataset contains wind speed and direction data measured by the GSFC Lidar Observatory for Wind (GLOW) at the Homestead site during the IHOP_2002 field project. Data are 10 minute averaged winds with 100 meter vertical resolution for altitudes below 3 km, and 200 meters vertical resolution for altitudes above 3 km. Data are in ASCII format.

title: GCIP/EOP Satellite: GOES-8 4-km CONUS Sector Satellite Data
summary: Digital GOES-8 4-km visible, infrared, and water vapor data from October 1995 to March 2001. Also, since November 1998 all five channels from GOES-8 are available. Data are in McIDAS AREA file format. These data cover the continental US.

title: MSU Mobile Radiosonde Data
summary: This data set contains temperature, moisture, and wind profiles from the WindSond radiosondes utilized in two mobile radiosonde systems operated by Mississippi State University as part of the Verification of the Origins of Rotation in Tornadoes Experiment-Southeast (VORTEX-SE) 2017 field season. These data are available in the original comma-delimited ASCII format or in the EOL Sounding Composite (ESC) columnar ASCII format.

title: COMET CASE 017 WSR-88D Storm Relative Velocity (third-lowest tilt angle) from Phoenix, AZ (IWA)
summary: This dataset contains the Storm Relative Velocity           (third-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the Phoenix, AZ (IWA)radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: WRF 4KM Forecast Imagery: Craig to Imperial [Dudhia (NCAR-MMM)]
summary: This dataset links to all five Weather Research and Forecasting Model (WRF) 4 kilometer forecast imagery datasets generated during the ICE-L project from Craig, CO to Imperial, NE. Companion datasets below contain vertical cross-sections of the following: Radar Reflectivity, Mixing Ratios, Relative Humidity, Equivalent Potential Temperature, and Vertical Velocity. All of the imagery is available to order in PNG format and it covers the time span from 2007-11-19 00:00:00 to 2007-12-21 23:59:59.

title: Sounding data from San Cristobal (Galapagos)
summary: This dataset contains high resolution upper air sounding data from San Cristobal in the Galapagos Islands. The dataset contains vertical profiles of pressure, wind speed and direction, air temperature, dew point temperature, relative humidity, and altitude. This data has undergone some quality control. See the README for more details.

title: ACE-ASIA Surface: Gosan(Kosan) Chemistry TSP Major Ions (Schauer)(ASCII)
summary: This data set includes the total suspended particulate (TSP) particle-phase concentrations of sulfate, nitrate, and ammonium ions and chloride collected from the Gosan Supersite located on Jeju Island, South Korea during ACE-ASIA. This data set contains a tab delimited ASCII text file. It can also be downloaded as a Microsoft Excel file.

title: Scanning Aerosol Backscatter Lidar (SABL) - NetCDF format [Morley, B. (NCAR/RSF)]
summary: This dataset contains Scanning Aerosol Backscatter Lidar (SABL) data obtained aboard the NCAR/NSF C-130 aircraft during the EPIC (Eastern Pacific Investigation of Climate Processes in the Coupled Ocean-Atmosphere System) project. The data are in netCDF format.

title: Multi-Network Composite Highest Resolution Radiosonde Data
summary: This data set contains a composite of the highest vertical resolution (i.e. the native  resolution) upper air sounding data from all sources for the Verification of the Origins of Rotation in Thunderstorms Experiment-Southeast 2016 (VORTEX-SE_2016) project. The composite includes 1488 soundings from all VORTEX-SE 2016 sounding systems (Purdue, ULM, NOAA/ATD, MSU iMet, MSU WindSond, and TTU) as well as from the National Weather Service.

title: COMET CASE 034 DIX radar.gif imagery
summary: This dataset contains DIX radar imagery. Data is archived as GIF files.

title: COMET CASE 018 WSR-88D Base Reflectivity (lowest tilt angle) from SIOUX FALLS, SD
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Base Reflectivity (lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  SIOUX FALLS, SD/Sioux Falls (FSD) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: Buoy University of Southern Mississippi (USM) Data
summary: This data set contains 30 minute resolution surface meteorological and oceanographic data in a single file. Data are from the University of Southern Mississippi Department of Marine Science buoy located in the Gulf of Mexico off the coast of Mississippi. These data were retrieved from the National Data Buoy Center (NDBC). There is 1 station in this data set. This data set covers the period from 1 June to 29 August 2005. The data are in space delimited ASCII format. NCAR/EOL has conducted no additional quality control on these data.

title: GOES-11 Leg1 KBJC-PANC 4km Ch1 Visible Satellite Imagery
summary: This dataset contains leg1 KBJC-PANC 4km Channel 1 Visible imagery from the GOES-11 satellite taken during the HIPPO-3 project. The imagery are in JPG format. The imagery cover the time span from 2010-03-09 13:07:00 to 2010-04-20 14:45:00.

title: HLY-09-02 TeraScan HRPT Satellite Data [Ashjian/LDEO]
summary: This dataset includes High Resolution Picture Transmission (HRPT) data from the SeaSpace TeraScan System. The data are from the NOAA-15, NOAA-17, NOAA-18 and NOAA-19 National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) Polar Orbiting Environmental Satellites (POES). The data are from the satellite passes that occurred over the Bering Sea during the Bering Sea Ecosystem Study-Bering Sea Integrated Ecosystem Research Program (BEST-BSIERP) 2009 0902 (late spring) cruise onboard the U.S. Coast Guard Cutter Healy. BEST-BSIERP together are the Bering Sea project. Most of the files are in TeraScan format, with some tif images included. The individual data files have been collected into tar files by day.

title: COMET CASE 029 NCEP's Nested Gridded Model (NGM).
summary: This dataset contains data from  NCEP's Nested Gridded Model (NGM). The model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecasts given every six hours going out 48 hours .  The data are archived in GRIB gridded files.

title: GCIP/LSA-NW 99 Upper Air: NWS Mandatory and Significant Level Sounding Data
summary: The GCIP/LSANW 99 Mandatory and Significant Level Sounding  data set contains sounding data extracted from the NOAA/FSL radiosonde database for 17 NWS sites over the GCIP LSA-North West region during the period from April 1999 to March 2000. Other sites also occasionally other sites also released radiosonde and are included. These data have not been changed or quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS.  Refer to the README file for more details.

title: COMET CASE 018 NCEP's Eta Model.
summary: This dataset contains data from  NCEP's Eta Model. Model runs are for 00Z and 12Z daily with forecast times every six hours from 00 to 48 hours.The data are archived in GRIB files.

title: JMA MRI Global 20km AGCM Output [JMA]
summary: This data set consists of output from the Japan Meteorological Agency - Meteorological Research Institute 20km Global AGCM for the period 1 April to 31 October for the years 2000 - 2006 in netCDF format. This data set includes hourly, 6-hourly, daily and monthly mean output for varying regions of North Africa. See the readme file for details.

title: ASOS 1-minute Data
summary: This data set contains the 1-minute resolution surface meteorological observations from the Automated Surface Observing System (ASOS) network of ~860 stations in the United States for the March-May 2017 period. These data were collected by the National Centers for Environmental Information (NCEI; formerly the National Climatic Data Center).

title: COMET CASE 024 WSR-88D Radial Velocity (lowest tilt angle) from WASHINGTON,DC
summary: This dataset contains the  WSR-88D Radial Velocity (lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the  WASHINGTON,DC (LWX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: PICARRO G1301-f In Situ Carbon dioxide (CO2) mixing ratio, Methane (CH4) data
summary: This dataset contains carbon dioxide (CO2) and methane (CH4) in situ mixing ratio observations collected by the PICARRO G1301-f aboard the NSF/NCAR C-130 during the Wintertime Investigation of Transport, Emission, and Reactivity (WINTER) project.

title: NEXRAD San Juan Imagery [/NCAR-EOL]
summary: This dataset contains gif imagery from the NEXRAD radar, taken during the Ice in Clouds Experiment - Tropical (ICE-T) project.

title: Thule Leaf Gas Exchange Salix and Dryas 2005
summary: This dataset includes measurements of Dryas integrifolia and Salix arctica leaf gas exchange made under conditions of saturating light, ambient CO2 and optimum temperature. Also included are leaf C and N concentrations and leaf d15N and d13C. Measurements were made at 5 sites near Thule (Pituffik), Greenland: 3 sites along a south-facing hill slope, the site of a warming x watering experiment and the site of a fertilization experiment. At the experimental sites, measurements were made in control plots, in plots that received the higher of two levels of infrared warming and in plots that were fertilized with 5 g N m-2 yr-1 applied as granular NH4NO3 and 2.5 g P m-2 yr-1 as granular P2O5 beginning in 2004. Coverage is from 20050708- 20050801.

title: COMET CASE 008 WSR-88D Three-hour Precipitation Estimate from Sacramento, CA (BBX)
summary: This dataset contains the Three-hour Precipitation Estimate data product archived from the Sacramento, CA (BBX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: ACE-1: Satellite NOAA-12 VIS Channel 2 Images (GIF)
summary: NOAA-12 POES Visible (VIS) Channel 2 imagery collected during the ACE-1 Intensive Operations in Hobart, Tasmania, via the Naval Postgraduate School (NPGS) portable SeaSpace Terrascan receiver system, then converted to GIF image format. These images consist of horizon to horizon scans at 4 km resolution, collected every overpass (typically 2 times per day). Digital Terrascan format files were collected by the NPGS from which these images were created.

title: COMET CASE 042 base reflectivity 1.45/1.5 degrees elevation angle from TOPEKA, KS/Alma
summary: This dataset contains the  data product archived from the  TOPEKA, KS/Alma (TWX) radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: AVHRR Polar Pathfinder Derived Satellite Products for SHEBA [Maslanik, J.]
summary: This dataset is a remote website that provides various satellite products for the SHEBA project. The site contains gridded data, animations, and tabular data available for viewing and downloading. More detailed information is at the site.

title: COMET CASE 044 base radial velocity, 124 nmi range, 0.50 degree elevation angle from LVX
summary: This dataset contains the  base radial velocity, 124 nmi range, 0.50 degree elevation angle data product archived from the  LOUISVILLE, KY/Fort Knox LVX radar. Data are archived in the NIDS format.

title: SAS Field Catalog Reports
summary: This dataset provides a link to the SAS Field Catalog Reports section. It includes a variety of reports that summarize campaign operations.

title: COMET CASE 006 WSI NIDS Radial Velocity (second-lowest tilt angle) from Green Bay, WI
summary: This dataset contains the velocity relative to radar (second-lowest tilt angle) data product archived from the WSI NIDS datastream for the Green Bay, WI radar. Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format.

title: Mobile Integrated Profiling System (MIPS) Microwave Profiling Radiometer Data [U Alabama]
summary: This dataset contains Mobile Integrated Profiling System (MIPS) Microwave Profiling Radiometer (MPR) Data from the University of Alabama in Huntsville.

title: Effects of Warming on a Polar Desert Ecosystem Replicate 1 [Epstein]
summary: This dataset measures the effects of warming on a polar desert ecosystem (Replicate 1) from 1995-2005 as part of the ITEX experiment. Each ecosystem has one warming and one control. Each experiment for each ecosystem has five replicates. This dataset includes only the top hit. For more information, please see the readme file.

title: ITOP.org
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: Surface PAM/ASTER 30-Minute Data (ASCII Format)
summary: This dataset contains 30-minute data collected during the Cooperative Atmospheric Surface Exchange Study 1997 (CASES-97) project from 11 April to 23 May 1997. These data are in ASCII format.

title: NCAR WRF Global Forecast System (GFS) Initial Conditions Forecast Products
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: COMET CASE 013 GOES-9 VIS at 4km
summary: This dataset contains GOES-9 VIS imagery at 4km resolution.  Data is archived as McIDAS AREA files.

title: NCEP/EMC U.S. Gridded Radar-Estimated Precipitation w/ no bias removal (4km)
summary: This dataset contains the National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP) Environmental Modeling Center (EMC) 4 KM GRIB radar estimate (no bias removal) RAD" data. A prototype
end_date: multi-sensor National Preciptation Analysis (NPA) has been developed at NCEP in cooperation with the Office of Hydrology (OH). This analysis merges two data sources that are currently being collected in real-time by OH and NCEP. Hourly digital precipitation (HDP) radar estimates are created by the WSR-88D Radar Product Generator on a 131 X 131 4-km grid centered over each radar site. Data analysis routines
minimum_latitude: including a bias correction of the radar estimates using rain gage data
minimum_longitude: have been adapted by NCEP on a national 4-km grid from algorithms developed by OH and executed regionally at NWS River Forecast Centers (RFC). This dataset only contains the NCEP 4 KM GRIB Data hourly
maximum_longitude: and daily radar estimate (no bias removal). 6-hourly data are generally available at 00Z
horizontal_resolution_id: and 18Z. Daily data are generally available at 12Z. Depending on the time period selected
vertical_resolution_id: all three datasets may or may not be available. Other NCEP 4 KM GRIB Data including gage-only analysis
current_version_id: and gage-only analysis using 24h accumulated ("RFC") data are available as independent datasets. Depending on the time period selected
language_id: all five types may or may not be available. Please see GCIP/EOP: Surface NCEP Ancillary Catalogue of Available GCIP Precipitation Data (NCEP/EMC). The format of the files is GRIB. The files are compressed using the UNIX "compress" command and "uncompress" must be used before decoding. This dataset is provided as is and was not quality controlled by UCAR/JOSS. Beginning 1 Jan 2002
point_of_contact_id:
the analysis grid has been changed to conform with the official NWS HRAP grid. File names have also been changed. See the readme provided with this dataset for details. As of April 2017 this data includes Alaska and Puerto Rico stations.

"

title: CMORPH 3-Hourly Precipitation Data
summary: This data set contains 0.25 degree resolution 3-hourly global CMORPH precipitation data during DYNAMO (August 2011 through March 2012). CMORPH is the CPC Morphing technique which derives precipitation estimates from low orbiter satellite microwave observations. The data are in binary format and were provided by NOAA/CPC.

title: NCAR CP3, C-Band Radar data set, DORADE Format
summary: This dataset contains C-band radar data collected by the NCAR CP3 radar during the Hawaiian Rainband Project (HaRP) from 11 July 1990 to 23 August 1990. The data are in DORADE format and are available as tar files (~500 MB per file).

title: MTSAT Water Vapor Imagery [NRL]
summary: This data set contains 30-minute MTSAT water vapor satellite imagery over the Western Pacific Ocean developed by NRL. The files are in jpg format.

title: Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics HRT Data in NetCDF format
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the NCAR Research Aviation Facility (RAF) King Air aircraft (Tail Number N312D) during the Mexico City Air Pollution study (MexCAPS) project. This dataset contains high rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in netCDF format.

title: MTSAT-1R Leg6 AGGH-PHKO Ch2 Thermal IR Satellite Imagery
summary: This dataset contains leg6 AGGH-PHKO Channel 2 thermal IR imagery from the MTSAT-1R satellite taken during the HIPPO-2 project. The imagery are in JPG format. The imagery cover the time span from 2009-11-05 17:30:00 to 2009-12-21 21:30:00.

title: GEM and TEM Model Simulations for Toolik Lake [McGuire, A. D.]
summary: This dataset contains the model output data of GEM and TEM simulations from 1920 to 2100 for Toolik Lake, Alaska. This dataset is available offline as a CD.

title: COMET CASE 010 GOES-8 WV at 8km
summary: This dataset contains GOES-8 WV imagery at 8km resolution.  Data is archived as McIDAS AREA files.

title: World Wide Lightning Location Network (WWLLN) Data
summary: This data set contains global lightning location data from the World Wide Lightning Location Network (WWLLN) for the DYNAMO time period. The data are in a comma-delimited ASCII format. These data were provided by Dr. Robert Holzworth at the University of Washington.

title: USCGC Healy HLY1001 SADCP Data 2010 for DBO5
summary: This dataset contains oceanographic SADCP profiles collected with an RDI Shipboard Acoustic Doppler Current Profiler. The data were collected aboard the USCGC Healy along the line DBO 5 (Barrow Canyon) on July 12-13, 2010. There is one MATLAB file containing the following parameters: time, position, east velocity, north velocity, current direction, current speed, and depth.

title: NOAA/NCEP GFS Model Forecast Imagery [NOAA/NCEP]
summary:
This data set contains the several forecast image products from the NOAA/NCEP GFS model. The products include 300mb heights/wind, 500mb heights/vorticity/wind, 700 mb heights/humidity/wind, 850mb heights/temperature/wind, mean sea level pressure/1000-500 mb thickness/precipitation, and surface winds/temperature/MSLP. The products are available every 6 hours out to the 180 hour forecast and every 12 hours from 180-204 hours. The images were created by NOAA/NCEP.

his data set contains imagery from the two PLOWS field phases, 6 February to 30 March 2009 and 14 October 2009 to 10 March 2010. No imagery are available for the period between the field phases.

title: ACE-ASIA Surface: GTS Surface Synoptic Observations
summary: The ACE-ASIA Surface: GTS Surface Synoptic Observations are online data.  Data is in GEMPAK format.

title: FAAM BAe-146 Upward, Downward, Forward, and Rear Video
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: High Rate (HRT - 1 sps) Navigation, State Parameter, and Microphysics Flight-Level Data
summary: This data set includes airborne measurements obtained from the NSF/NCAR QueenAir, A-80 aircraft (Tail Number N304D) during theMountain-Induced Convection (MIC) project. This dataset contains high rate navigation, state parameter, and microphysics flight-level data in netCDF format.

title: HLY-02-03 ADCP Data (2-min Averages) [Muenchow, A.]
summary: The United States Coast Guard Cutter (USCGC) Healy contains a 75-kHz phased-array Acoustic Doppler Current Profiler (ADCP) (Ocean Surveyor) mounted under the hull to transmit and receive echos of acoustic pulses from which to estimate vertical profiles of horizontal currents. Attitude information such as heading, pitch, and roll is provided by an Ashtech ADU2-3DGPS receiver while position data are provided by a Trimble Centurion p-code DGPS system. These data streams provide earth-referenced absolute horizontal currents and their vertical variations from about 20-m below the surface to the bottom or about 400-m depth. These data are 2 minute averages.

title: UW Madison HSRL Data Archives
summary: This dataset provides a link to the UW Madison HSRL Data Archives.

title: PCAPS ISS Ceilometer Data
summary: This dataset contains ceilometer data collected by the NCAR/EOL Integrated Sounding System (ISS) ceilometer during the Persistent Cold-Air Pool Study (PCAPS) between 01 December 2010 and 17 February 2011. These data are in daily tar files containing raw ASCII format ceilometer data and have not been quality controlled.

title: TOGA COARE soundings from Hong Kong
summary: This dataset consists of sounding data from King's Park, Hong Kong (WMO 45004) which was operated by the Hong Kong Royal Observatory. Soundings were taken twice daily (00 and 12 UTC) during the IOP. UCAR/JOSS conducted no quality control on these data. This dataset inlcudes pressure, temperature, dew point, relative humidity, wind speed, wind direction, and altitude taken at 10 second vertical intervals. See station README file for details. NOTE: This dataset has been updated (4/30/2002) with corrected data for the humidity measurement errors of the Vaisala RS 80 radiosonde (Wang et al 2002). Please see the README for additional information.

title: COMET CASE 005 WSI NIDS 2.5 degree Radial Velocity from Pittsburgh, PA
summary: This dataset contains the 2.5 degree Radial Velocity data product archived from the WSI NIDS datastream for the Pittsburgh, PA radar. Data are archived in the original WSI NIDS format, at a frequency of 10 minutes.

title: COMET CASE 008 GOES-9 VIS at 1km
summary: This dataset contains GOES-9 VIS imagery at 1km resolution. Data is archived as McIDAS AREA files.

title: AWC GTG Forecast Product Imagery
summary: This dataset provides a link to the DC-3 Field Catalog Model Products section which includes AWC GTG Forecast Product Imagery

title: TRMM Real-time Rainfall Analyses (3-h)
summary: NULL
archive_note: This dataset links to supplemental information for the project.

title: Bureau of Meteorology Hobart Radiosonde Data (ESC format)
summary: The Australian Bureau of Meteorology routinely releases radiosondes from Hobart (WMO 94975) which is on the southeastern end of the island of Tasmania. During the DEEPWAVE field phase, soundings were routinely released twice daily (00 and 12 UTC) and there were also some occasional special releases. This data set includes the quality controlled Hobart soundings released for the DEEPWAVE field phase (28 May to 31 July 2014). A total of 137 quality controlled, high resolution (2-second) soundings are contained in the final DEEPWAVE data set.

title: NEXRAD Radar Reflectivity and Velocity Imagery [NCAR/EOL]
summary: This dataset contains NEXRAD radar reflectivity and velocity imagery for storm-specific areas within the RAINEX area of interest, available at roughly 5 minute intervals.

title: 2019 Autumn Tree Phenology Data
summary: This dataset provides a link to the National Phenology Network archive for the CHEESEHEAD (WLEF/Park Falls, WI) Autumn Tree Phenology Observations in 2019.
